pokemon.pokedexY: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokémon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokémon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokémon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.

pokemon.name: Lickitung
pokemon.pokedexX: Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.

pokemon.name: Koffing
pokemon.pokedexX: Its thin, filmy body is filled with gases that cause constant sniffles, coughs and teary eyes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If Koffing becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This Pokémon may also overinflate its round body, then explode.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Koffing embodies toxic substances. It mixes the toxins with raw garbage to set off a chemical reaction that results in a terribly powerful poison gas. The higher the temperature, the more gas is concocted by this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Weezing
pokemon.pokedexX: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.
pokemon.pokedexY: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Weezing loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This Pokémon will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Weezing alternately shrinks and inflates its twin bodies to mix together toxic gases inside. The more the gases are mixed, the more powerful the toxins become. The Pokémon also becomes more putrid.

pokemon.name: Rhyhorn
pokemon.pokedexX: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokémon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Rhyhorn's brain is very small. It is so dense, while on a run it forgets why it started running in the first place. It apparently remembers sometimes if it demolishes something.

pokemon.name: Rhydon
pokemon.pokedexX: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexY: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Rhydon's horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This Pokémon's hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don't leave a scratch.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Rhydon has a horn that serves as a drill. It is used for destroying rocks and boulders. This Pokémon occasionally rams into streams of magma, but the armor-like hide prevents it from feeling the heat.

pokemon.name: Chansey
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said to deliver happiness. Being compassionate, it shares its eggs with injured people.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lays several eggs in a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Chansey lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Chansey lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.

pokemon.name: Tangela
pokemon.pokedexX: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole  life long.
pokemon.pokedexY: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Tangela's vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tangela's vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.

pokemon.name: Kangaskhan
pokemon.pokedexX: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.

pokemon.name: Horsea
pokemon.pokedexX: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Horsea eats small insects and moss off of rocks. If the ocean current turns fast, this Pokémon anchors itself by wrapping its tail around rocks or coral to prevent being washed away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If Horsea senses danger, it will reflexively spray a dense black ink from its mouth and try to escape. This Pokémon swims by cleverly flapping the fin on its back.

pokemon.name: Seadra
pokemon.pokedexX: Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Seadra sleeps after wriggling itself between the branches of coral. Those trying to harvest coral are occasionally stung by this Pokémon's poison barbs if they fail to notice it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Seadra generates whirlpools by spinning its body. The whirlpools are strong enough to swallow even fishing boats. This Pokémon weakens prey with these currents, then swallows it whole.

pokemon.name: Goldeen
pokemon.pokedexX: It swims at a steady 5 knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the water dancer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Goldeen is a very beautiful Pokémon with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don't let your guard down around this Pokémon-it could ram you powerfully with its horn.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Goldeen loves swimming wild and free in rivers and ponds. If one of these Pokémon is placed in an aquarium, it will shatter even the thickest glass with one ram of its horn and make its escape.

pokemon.name: Seaking
pokemon.pokedexX: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in  streams with its horn. It defends its eggs with  its life.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In the autumn, Seaking males can be seen performing courtship dances in riverbeds to woo females. During this season, this Pokémon's body coloration is at its most beautiful.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Seaking is very protective of its eggs. The male and female will take turns patrolling around their nest and eggs. The guarding of eggs by these Pokémon goes on for over a month.

pokemon.name: Staryu
pokemon.pokedexX: Even if its body is torn, it can regenerate as long as the glowing central core remains intact.
pokemon.pokedexY: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night,  its central core flashes with a red light.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Staryu's center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pokémon look like the stars in the sky.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Staryu apparently communicates with the stars in the night sky by flashing the red core at the center of its body. If parts of its body are torn, this Pokémon simply regenerates the missing pieces and limbs.

pokemon.name: Starmie
pokemon.pokedexX: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.
pokemon.pokedexY: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends  mysterious radio signals into the night sky.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Starmie's center section-the core-glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this Pokémon has been given the nickname "the gem of the sea."
pokemon.pokedexAS: Starmie swims through water by spinning its star-shaped body as if it were a propeller on a ship. The core at the center of this Pokémon's body glows in seven colors.

pokemon.name: Mr. Mime
pokemon.pokedexX: Emanations from its fingertips solidify the air into invisible walls that repel even harsh attacks.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once the watchers are convinced, the unseeable thing exists as if it were real.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once the watchers are convinced, the unseeable thing exists as if it were real.

pokemon.name: Scyther
pokemon.pokedexX: It tears and shreds prey with its wickedly sharp scythes. It very rarely spreads its wings to fly.
pokemon.pokedexY: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes,  moving too fast for the human eye to track.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Scyther is blindingly fast. Its blazing speed enhances the effectiveness of the twin scythes on its forearms. This Pokémon's scythes are so effective, they can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Scyther is blindingly fast. Its blazing speed enhances the effectiveness of the twin scythes on its forearms. This Pokémon's scythes are so effective, they can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.

pokemon.name: Jynx
pokemon.pokedexX: It wiggles its hips as it walks. It can  cause people to dance in unison with it.
pokemon.pokedexY: It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Jynx walks rhythmically, swaying and shaking its hips as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without giving any thought to what they are doing.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Jynx walks rhythmically, swaying and shaking its hips as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without giving any thought to what they are doing.

pokemon.name: Electabuzz
pokemon.pokedexX: Electricity runs across the surface of its body. In darkness, its entire body glows a whitish blue.
pokemon.pokedexY: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When a storm arrives, gangs of this Pokémon compete with each other to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning bolts. Some towns use Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When a storm arrives, gangs of this Pokémon compete with each other to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning bolts. Some towns use Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.

pokemon.name: Magmar
pokemon.pokedexX: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather's body temperature is nearly 2,200 degree Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexY: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In battle, Magmar blows out intensely hot flames from all over its body to intimidate its opponent. This Pokémon's fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in its surroundings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In battle, Magmar blows out intensely hot flames from all over its body to intimidate its opponent. This Pokémon's fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Pinsir
pokemon.pokedexX: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.
pokemon.pokedexY: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack.  During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokémon's movements turn sluggish in cold places.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Pinsir has a pair of massive horns. Protruding from the surface of these horns are thorns. These thorns are driven deeply into the foe's body when the pincer closes, making it tough for the foe to escape.

pokemon.name: Tauros
pokemon.pokedexX: After heightening its will to fight by whipping itself with its three tails, it charges at full speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it is about to tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.

pokemon.name: Magikarp
pokemon.pokedexX: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.
pokemon.pokedexY: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Magikarp is a pathetic excuse for a Pokémon that is only capable of flopping and splashing. This behavior prompted scientists to undertake research into it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Magikarp is virtually useless in battle as it can only splash around. As a result, it is considered to be weak. However, it is actually a very hardy Pokémon that can survive in any body of water no matter how polluted it is.

pokemon.name: Gyarados
pokemon.pokedexX: In ancient literature, there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared.
pokemon.pokedexY: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Once Gyarados goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn't calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this Pokémon's rampages lasting a whole month.

pokemon.name: Lapras
pokemon.pokedexX: They have gentle hearts. Because they rarely fight, many have been caught. Their number has dwindled.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this Pokémon is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.
pokemon.pokedexAS: People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this Pokémon is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.

pokemon.name: Ditto
pokemon.pokedexX: It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ditto rearranges its cell structure to transform itself into other shapes. However, if it tries to transform itself into something by relying on its memory, this Pokémon manages to get details wrong.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ditto rearranges its cell structure to transform itself into other shapes. However, if it tries to transform itself into something by relying on its memory, this Pokémon manages to get details wrong.

pokemon.name: Eevee
pokemon.pokedexX: A rare Pokémon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.
pokemon.pokedexY: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various stones causes this Pokémon to evolve.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various stones causes this Pokémon to evolve.

pokemon.name: Vaporeon
pokemon.pokedexX: It prefers beautiful shores. With cells similar to water molecules, it could melt in water.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has evolved to be suitable for an aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous mutation and grew fins and gills that allow it to live underwater. This Pokémon has the ability to freely control water.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Vaporeon underwent a spontaneous mutation and grew fins and gills that allow it to live underwater. This Pokémon has the ability to freely control water.

pokemon.name: Jolteon
pokemon.pokedexX: Every hair on its body starts to stand sharply on  end if it becomes charged with electricity.
pokemon.pokedexY: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10,000-volt lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Jolteon's cells generate a low level of electricity. This power is amplified by the static electricity of its fur, enabling the Pokémon to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is made of electrically charged needles.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Jolteon's cells generate a low level of electricity. This power is amplified by the static electricity of its fur, enabling the Pokémon to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is made of electrically charged needles.

pokemon.name: Flareon
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a flame sac in its body. Its body temperature  tops 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit before battle.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blows out flames of nearly 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Flareon's fluffy fur has a functional purpose-it releases heat into the air so that its body does not get excessively hot. This Pokémon's body temperature can rise to a maximum of 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Flareon's fluffy fur has a functional purpose-it releases heat into the air so that its body does not get excessively hot. This Pokémon's body temperature can rise to a maximum of 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Porygon
pokemon.pokedexX: A manmade Pokémon that came about as a result of research. It is programmed with only basic motions.
pokemon.pokedexY: A Pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. It is capable of moving freely in cyberspace.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Porygon is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying.

pokemon.name: Omanyte
pokemon.pokedexX: A prehistoric Pokémon that lived in the primordial sea, it swims by twisting its 10 tentacles about.
pokemon.pokedexY: Revived from an ancient fossil, this Pokémon uses air stored in its shell to sink and rise in water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Omanyte is one of the ancient and long-since-extinct Pokémon that have been regenerated from fossils by people. If attacked by an enemy, it withdraws itself inside its hard shell.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Omanyte is one of the ancient and long-since-extinct Pokémon that have been regenerated from fossils by people. If attacked by an enemy, it withdraws itself inside its hard shell.

pokemon.name: Omastar
pokemon.pokedexX: Its tentacles are highly developed as if they are hands and feet. As soon as it ensnares prey, it bites.
pokemon.pokedexY: Once wrapped around its prey, it never lets go. It eats the prey by tearing at it with sharp fangs.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Omastar uses its tentacles to capture its prey. It is believed to have become extinct because its shell grew too large and heavy, causing its movements to become too slow and ponderous.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Omastar uses its tentacles to capture its prey. It is believed to have become extinct because its shell grew too large and heavy, causing its movements to become too slow and ponderous.

pokemon.name: Kabuto
pokemon.pokedexX: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.
pokemon.pokedexY: This Pokémon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Kabuto is a Pokémon that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered. The Pokémon has not changed at all for 300 million years.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kabuto is a Pokémon that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered. The Pokémon has not changed at all for 300 million years.

pokemon.name: Kabutops
pokemon.pokedexX: In the water, it tucks in its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.
pokemon.pokedexY: A slim and fast swimmer. It slices its prey with its sharp sickles and drinks the body fluids.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.

pokemon.name: Aerodactyl
pokemon.pokedexX: It was regenerated from a dinosaur's genetic matter that was found in amber. It flies with high-pitched cries.
pokemon.pokedexY: This vicious Pokémon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.

pokemon.name: Snorlax
pokemon.pokedexX: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of  food every day. When it is done eating, it goes  promptly to sleep.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.

pokemon.name: Articuno
pokemon.pokedexX: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
pokemon.pokedexY: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Articuno is a legendary bird Pokémon that can control ice. The flapping of its wings chills the air. As a result, it is said that when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Articuno is a legendary bird Pokémon that can control ice. The flapping of its wings chills the air. As a result, it is said that when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.

pokemon.name: Zapdos
pokemon.pokedexX: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexY: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in  thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. The Pokémon gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. The Pokémon gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: Moltres
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said to be the legendary bird Pokémon of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare of flames.
pokemon.pokedexY: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Moltres is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control fire. If this Pokémon is injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Moltres is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control fire. If this Pokémon is injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.

pokemon.name: Dratini
pokemon.pokedexX: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.
pokemon.pokedexY: This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.

pokemon.name: Dragonair
pokemon.pokedexX: Its crystalline orbs appear to give this Pokémon the power to freely control the weather.
pokemon.pokedexY: A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. It is said to have the ability to change the weather.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity by discharging energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity by discharging energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.

pokemon.name: Dragonite
pokemon.pokedexX: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.

pokemon.name: Mewtwo
pokemon.pokedexX: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.
pokemon.pokedexY: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

pokemon.name: Mew
pokemon.pokedexX: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

pokemon.name: Chikorita
pokemon.pokedexX: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up sunrays.
pokemon.pokedexY: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

pokemon.name: Bayleef
pokemon.pokedexX: A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.
pokemon.pokedexY: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

pokemon.name: Meganium
pokemon.pokedexX: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.
pokemon.pokedexY: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The fragrance of Meganium's flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The fragrance of Meganium's flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.

pokemon.name: Cyndaquil
pokemon.pokedexX: It is timid, and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

pokemon.name: Quilava
pokemon.pokedexX: Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes
pokemon.pokedexY: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

pokemon.name: Typhlosion
pokemon.pokedexX: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

pokemon.name: Totodile
pokemon.pokedexX: It is small but rough and tough. It won't hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

pokemon.name: Croconaw
pokemon.pokedexX: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexY: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

pokemon.name: Feraligatr
pokemon.pokedexX: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

pokemon.name: Sentret
pokemon.pokedexX: When acting as a lookout, it warns others of danger by screeching and hitting the ground with its tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

pokemon.name: Furret
pokemon.pokedexX: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

pokemon.name: Hoothoot
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.
pokemon.pokedexY: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth's rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth's rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.

pokemon.name: Noctowl
pokemon.pokedexX: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.

pokemon.name: Ledyba
pokemon.pokedexX: When the weather turns cold, lots of Ledyba gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ledyba secretes an aromatic fluid from where its legs join its body. This fluid is used for communicating with others. This Pokémon conveys its feelings to others by altering the fluid's scent.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ledyba secretes an aromatic fluid from where its legs join its body. This fluid is used for communicating with others. This Pokémon conveys its feelings to others by altering the fluid's scent.

pokemon.name: Ledian
pokemon.pokedexX: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.
pokemon.pokedexY: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller  depending on the number of stars in the night sky.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this-the Pokémon uses the light of the stars as its energy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this-the Pokémon uses the light of the stars as its energy.

pokemon.name: Spinarak
pokemon.pokedexX: It spins a web using fine--but durable--thread. It then waits patiently for prey to be trapped.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web's strands.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web's strands.

pokemon.name: Ariados
pokemon.pokedexX: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It's hard to tell which end is which.
pokemon.pokedexY: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ariados's feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. This Pokémon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ariados's feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. This Pokémon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.

pokemon.name: Crobat
pokemon.pokedexX: It flies so silently through the dark on its four wings that it may not be noticed even when nearby.
pokemon.pokedexY: Having four wings allows it to fly more quickly and quietly so it can sneak up on prey without its noticing.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If this Pokémon is flying by fluttering only a pair of wings on either the forelegs or hind legs, it's proof that Crobat has been flying a long distance. It switches the wings it uses if it is tired.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Crobat sneaks up on its intended prey using wings that barely make a sound. This Pokémon rests by hanging on a tree branch with its rear legs that serve as wings.

pokemon.name: Chinchou
pokemon.pokedexX: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.
pokemon.pokedexY: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Chinchou lets loose positive and negative electrical charges from its two antennas to make its prey faint. This Pokémon flashes its electric lights to exchange signals with others.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Chinchou's two antennas are filled with cells that generate strong electricity. This Pokémon's cells create so much electrical power, it even makes itself tingle slightly.

pokemon.name: Lanturn
pokemon.pokedexX: Lanturn's light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed "The Deep-Sea Star."
pokemon.pokedexY: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light.  With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon  swallows it in a single gulp.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lanturn is nicknamed "the deep-sea star" for its illuminated antenna. This Pokémon produces light by causing a chemical reaction between bacteria and its bodily fluids inside the antenna.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lanturn is known to emit light. If you peer down into the dark sea from a ship at night, you can sometimes see this Pokémon's light rising from the depths where it swims. It gives the sea an appearance of a starlit night.

pokemon.name: Pichu
pokemon.pokedexX: It plays with others by touching tails and setting off sparks. This appears to be a test of courage.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Pichu charges itself with electricity more easily on days with thunderclouds or when the air is very dry. You can hear the crackling of static electricity coming off this Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Pichu plays with others, it may short out electricity with another Pichu, creating a shower of sparks. In that event, this Pokémon will begin crying, startled by the flash of sparks.

pokemon.name: Cleffa
pokemon.pokedexX: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.
pokemon.pokedexY: Many appear when the night skies are filled with shooting stars. They disappear with sunrise.
pokemon.pokedexOR: On nights with many shooting stars, Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance through the night and stop only at the break of day, when these Pokémon quench their thirst with the morning dew.
pokemon.pokedexAS: On nights with many shooting stars, Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance through the night and stop only at the break of day, when these Pokémon quench their thirst with the morning dew.

pokemon.name: Igglybuff
pokemon.pokedexX: Instead of walking with its short legs, it moves around by bouncing on its soft, tender body.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Igglybuff's vocal cords are not sufficiently developed. It would hurt its throat if it were to sing too much. This Pokémon gargles with freshwater from a clean stream.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Igglybuff has a soft and plushy body that feels very much like a marshmallow. From this body wafts a gently sweet fragrance that soothes and calms the emotions of its foes.

pokemon.name: Togepi
pokemon.pokedexX: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.
pokemon.pokedexY: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.
pokemon.pokedexOR: As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.

pokemon.name: Togetic
pokemon.pokedexX: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.
pokemon.pokedexY: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.

pokemon.name: Natu
pokemon.pokedexX: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.
pokemon.pokedexY: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Natu cannot fly because its wings are not yet fully grown. If your eyes meet with this Pokémon's eyes, it will stare back intently at you. But if you move even slightly, it will hop away to safety.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Natu has a highly developed jumping ability. The Pokémon flaps and leaps onto tree branches that are taller than grown-up people to pick at the tree's new shoots.

pokemon.name: Xatu
pokemon.pokedexX: Once it begins to meditate at sunrise, the entire day will pass before it will move again.
pokemon.pokedexY: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Xatu stands rooted and still in one spot all day long. People believe that this Pokémon does so out of fear of the terrible things it has foreseen in the future.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Xatu is known to stand motionless while staring at the sun all day long. Some people revere it as a mystical Pokémon out of their belief that Xatu is in possession of the power to see into the future.

pokemon.name: Mareep
pokemon.pokedexX: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.
pokemon.pokedexY: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mareep's fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mareep's fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.

pokemon.name: Flaaffy
pokemon.pokedexX: Its fluffy fleece easily stores electricity. Its rubbery hide keeps it from being electrocuted.
pokemon.pokedexY: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity,  its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Flaaffy's wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Flaaffy's wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.

pokemon.name: Ampharos
pokemon.pokedexX: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
pokemon.pokedexY: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from  far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

pokemon.name: Bellossom
pokemon.pokedexX: Bellossom gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.
pokemon.pokedexY: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When Bellossom gets exposed to plenty of sunlight, the leaves ringing its body begin to spin around. This Pokémon's dancing is renowned in the southern lands.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A Bellossom grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly Gloom-the more stinky the better. At night, this Pokémon closes its petals and goes to sleep.

pokemon.name: Marill
pokemon.pokedexX: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.
pokemon.pokedexY: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Marill's oil-filled tail acts much like a life preserver. If you see just its tail bobbing on the water's surface, it's a sure indication that this Pokémon is diving beneath the water to feed on aquatic plants.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When fishing for food at the edge of a fast-running stream, Marill wraps its tail around the trunk of a tree. This Pokémon's tail is flexible and configured to stretch.

pokemon.name: Azumarill
pokemon.pokedexX: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.
pokemon.pokedexY: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it's in the water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Azumarill's long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air balloons if it spots a drowning Pokémon. The air balloons enable the Pokémon in trouble to breathe.

pokemon.name: Sudowoodo
pokemon.pokedexX: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.
pokemon.pokedexY: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates  water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pokémon is easily identified as a fake during the winter.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pokémon is easily identified as a fake during the winter.

pokemon.name: Politoed
pokemon.pokedexX: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.
pokemon.pokedexY: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The curled hair on Politoed's head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The curled hair on Politoed's head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.

pokemon.name: Hoppip
pokemon.pokedexX: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.
pokemon.pokedexY: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

pokemon.name: Skiploom
pokemon.pokedexX: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.
pokemon.pokedexY: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Skiploom's flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Skiploom's flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

pokemon.name: Jumpluff
pokemon.pokedexX: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

pokemon.name: Aipom
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Aipom's tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Aipom's tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.

pokemon.name: Sunkern
pokemon.pokedexX: It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

pokemon.name: Sunflora
pokemon.pokedexX: As the hot season approaches, the petals on this Pokémon's face become more vivid and lively.
pokemon.pokedexY: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

pokemon.name: Yanma
pokemon.pokedexX: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won't miss prey--even those behind it.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

pokemon.name: Wooper
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
pokemon.pokedexY: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

pokemon.name: Quagsire
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river's bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexY: This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

pokemon.name: Espeon
pokemon.pokedexX: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent's next move.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its fur is so sensitive, it can feel minute shifts in the air and predict the weather...and its foes' thoughts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.

pokemon.name: Umbreon
pokemon.pokedexX: The light of the moon changed Eevee's genetic structure. It lurks in darkness for prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it's filled with a mysterious power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon's waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon's waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

pokemon.name: Murkrow
pokemon.pokedexX: It hides any shiny object it finds in a secret location. Murkrow and Meowth loot one another's stashes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.

pokemon.name: Slowking
pokemon.pokedexX: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
pokemon.pokedexY: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke's head and unlocked an extraordinary power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.

pokemon.name: Misdreavus
pokemon.pokedexX: It gets nourishment from fear that it absorbs into its red orbs. In daytime, it sleeps in darkness.
pokemon.pokedexY: It likes playing mischievous tricks, such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.

pokemon.name: Unown
pokemon.pokedexX: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.
pokemon.pokedexY: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

pokemon.name: Wobbuffet
pokemon.pokedexX: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to build up its counterstrike.
pokemon.pokedexY: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If two or more Wobbuffet meet, they will turn competitive and try to outdo each other's endurance. However, they may try to see which one can endure the longest without food. Trainers need to beware of this habit.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wobbuffet does nothing but endure attacks-it won't attack on its own. However, it won't endure an attack on its tail. When that happens, the Pokémon will try to take the foe with it using Destiny Bond.

pokemon.name: Girafarig
pokemon.pokedexX: While it sleeps, the head on is tail keeps watch. The tail doesn't need to sleep.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Girafarig's rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Girafarig's rear head contains a tiny brain that is too small for thinking. However, the rear head doesn't need to sleep, so it can keep watch over its surroundings 24 hours a day.

pokemon.name: Pineco
pokemon.pokedexX: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.
pokemon.pokedexY: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.

pokemon.name: Forretress
pokemon.pokedexX: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.
pokemon.pokedexY: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell's inside cannot be seen.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell's inside cannot be seen.

pokemon.name: Dunsparce
pokemon.pokedexX: When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

pokemon.name: Gligar
pokemon.pokedexX: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

pokemon.name: Steelix
pokemon.pokedexX: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.
pokemon.pokedexY: It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

pokemon.name: Snubbull
pokemon.pokedexX: It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.
pokemon.pokedexY: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.

pokemon.name: Granbull
pokemon.pokedexX: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.

pokemon.name: Qwilfish
pokemon.pokedexX: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.
pokemon.pokedexY: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.

pokemon.name: Scizor
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets ahold of into bits.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

pokemon.name: Shuckle
pokemon.pokedexX: The berries stored in its jar-like shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.
pokemon.pokedexY: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

pokemon.name: Heracross
pokemon.pokedexX: This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies, then lifts and throws them.
pokemon.pokedexY: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe's grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Heracross has sharp claws on its feet. These are planted firmly into the ground or the bark of a tree, giving the Pokémon a secure and solid footing to forcefully fling away foes with its proud horn.

pokemon.name: Sneasel
pokemon.pokedexX: It feeds on eggs stolen from nests. Its sharply hooked claws rip vulnerable spots on prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokémon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokémon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.

pokemon.name: Teddiursa
pokemon.pokedexX: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they're soaked with honey.
pokemon.pokedexY: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

pokemon.name: Ursaring
pokemon.pokedexX: With its ability to distinguish any aroma, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.
pokemon.pokedexY: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at  climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

pokemon.name: Slugma
pokemon.pokedexX: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Molten magma courses throughout Slugma's circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Slugma does not have any blood in its body. Instead, intensely hot magma circulates throughout this Pokémon's body, carrying essential nutrients and oxygen to its organs.

pokemon.name: Magcargo
pokemon.pokedexX: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Magcargo's shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile-just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Magcargo's body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Water is vaporized on contact. If this Pokémon is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

pokemon.name: Swinub
pokemon.pokedexX: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.

pokemon.name: Piloswine
pokemon.pokedexX: Although its legs are short, its rugged hooves prevent it from slipping, even on icy ground.
pokemon.pokedexY: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

pokemon.name: Corsola
pokemon.pokedexX: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.
pokemon.pokedexY: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral  branches lose their color and deteriorate in  dirty water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Clusters of Corsola congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller Pokémon. When the water temperature falls, this Pokémon migrates to the southern seas.

pokemon.name: Remoraid
pokemon.pokedexX: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike moving prey from more than 300 feet away.
pokemon.pokedexY: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a  Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.

pokemon.name: Octillery
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them  before attacking.
pokemon.pokedexY: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles,  then smashes them with its rock-hard head.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.

pokemon.name: Delibird
pokemon.pokedexX: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.
pokemon.pokedexY: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Delibird carries its food bundled up in its tail. There once was a famous explorer who managed to reach the peak of the world's highest mountain, thanks to one of these Pokémon sharing its food.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Delibird carries its food bundled up in its tail. There once was a famous explorer who managed to reach the peak of the world's highest mountain, thanks to one of these Pokémon sharing its food.

pokemon.name: Mantine
pokemon.pokedexX: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can fly over 300 feet out of the water from the surface of the ocean.
pokemon.pokedexY: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores  Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.
pokemon.pokedexOR: On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea's waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the Remoraid that hitches rides.
pokemon.pokedexAS: On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea's waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the Remoraid that hitches rides.

pokemon.name: Skarmory
pokemon.pokedexX: After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns.
pokemon.pokedexY: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor,  it flies at speeds over 180 mph.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Skarmory is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This Pokémon flies at close to 190 mph. It slashes foes with its wings that possess swordlike cutting edges.
