pokemon.pokedexAS: Skarmory's steel wings become tattered and bashed in from repeated battles. Once a year, the battered wings grow back completely, restoring the cutting edges to their pristine state.

pokemon.name: Houndour
pokemon.pokedexX: Around dawn, its ominous howl echoes through the area to announce that this is its territory.
pokemon.pokedexY: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon's remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon's remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.

pokemon.name: Houndoom
pokemon.pokedexX: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.
pokemon.pokedexY: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins.  If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

pokemon.name: Kingdra
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.
pokemon.pokedexY: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Kingdra lives at extreme ocean depths that are otherwise uninhabited. It has long been believed that the yawning of this Pokémon creates spiraling ocean currents.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kingdra sleeps on the seafloor where it is otherwise devoid of life. When a storm arrives, the Pokémon is said to awaken and wander about in search of prey.

pokemon.name: Phanpy
pokemon.pokedexX: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Phanpy uses its long nose to shower itself. When others gather around, they thoroughly douse each other with water. These Pokémon can be seen drying their soaking-wet bodies at the edge of water.

pokemon.name: Donphan
pokemon.pokedexX: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its Tackle is strong enough to knock down a house.
pokemon.pokedexY: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow,
pokemon.pokedexOR: Donphan's favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can't stop very easily.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If Donphan were to tackle with its hard body, even a house could be destroyed. Using its massive strength, the Pokémon helps clear rock and mud slides that block mountain trails.

pokemon.name: Porygon2
pokemon.pokedexX: Further research enhanced its abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.
pokemon.pokedexY: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Porygon2 was created by humans using the power of science. The man-made Pokémon has been endowed with artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Porygon2 was created by humans using the power of science. The man-made Pokémon has been endowed with artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.

pokemon.name: Stantler
pokemon.pokedexX: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.
pokemon.pokedexY: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Stantler's magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Stantler's magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

pokemon.name: Smeargle
pokemon.pokedexX: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.
pokemon.pokedexY: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Smeargle marks the boundaries of its territory using a body fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. Over 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Smeargle marks the boundaries of its territory using a body fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. Over 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.

pokemon.name: Tyrogue
pokemon.pokedexX: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.
pokemon.pokedexY: To brush up on its fighting skills, it will challenge anyone. It has a very strong competitive spirit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.

pokemon.name: Hitmontop
pokemon.pokedexX: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by 10.
pokemon.pokedexY: If you are enchanted by its smooth, dance-like kicks, you may get a closer experience with one than you'd like.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.

pokemon.name: Smoochum
pokemon.pokedexX: Its lips are the most sensitive part of its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.
pokemon.pokedexY: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.

pokemon.name: Elekid
pokemon.pokedexX: It generates electricity by whirling its arms. However, it can't store the energy it makes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Spinning its arms around to generate electricity makes the area between its horns shine light blue.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Elekid stores electricity in its body. If it touches metal and accidentally discharges all its built-up electricity, this Pokémon begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Elekid stores electricity in its body. If it touches metal and accidentally discharges all its built-up electricity, this Pokémon begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.

pokemon.name: Magby
pokemon.pokedexX: It's small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body's heat can top 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Magby's state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Magby's state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

pokemon.name: Miltank
pokemon.pokedexX: If it is around babies, the milk it produces contains much more nutrition than usual.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Miltank gives over five gallons of milk on a daily basis. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can't drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Miltank gives over five gallons of milk on a daily basis. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can't drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.

pokemon.name: Blissey
pokemon.pokedexX: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
pokemon.pokedexY: This kindhearted Pokémon nurses sick Pokémon to health. It senses feelings of sadness.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Blissey senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this Pokémon will rush over to a sad person, no matter how far away, to share a Lucky Egg that brings a smile to any face.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Blissey senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this Pokémon will rush over to a sad person, no matter how far away, to share a Lucky Egg that brings a smile to any face.

pokemon.name: Raikou
pokemon.pokedexX: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.
pokemon.pokedexY: This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity
pokemon.pokedexOR: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

pokemon.name: Entei
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

pokemon.name: Suicune
pokemon.pokedexX: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.
pokemon.pokedexY: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

pokemon.name: Larvitar
pokemon.pokedexX: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it falls asleep so it can grow.
pokemon.pokedexY: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.

pokemon.name: Pupitar
pokemon.pokedexX: Its body is as hard as bedrock. By venting pressurized gas, it can launch itself like a rocket.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable-it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable-it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

pokemon.name: Tyranitar
pokemon.pokedexX: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries  rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

pokemon.name: Lugia
pokemon.pokedexX: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lugia's wings pack devastating power-a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lugia's wings pack devastating power-a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

pokemon.name: Ho-Oh
pokemon.pokedexX: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.
pokemon.pokedexY: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-colored wings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ho-Oh's feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ho-Oh's feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

pokemon.name: Celebi
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

pokemon.name: Treecko
pokemon.pokedexX: It quickly scales even vertical walls. It senses humidity with its tail to predict the next day's weather.
pokemon.pokedexY: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Treecko is cool, calm, and collected-it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this Pokémon, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

pokemon.name: Grovyle
pokemon.pokedexX: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.
pokemon.pokedexY: It leaps from tree branch to tree branch quite swiftly. It shows astounding agility.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon adeptly flies from branch to branch in trees. In a forest, no Pokémon can ever hope to catch a fleeing Grovyle however fast they may be.

pokemon.name: Sceptile
pokemon.pokedexX: The leaves on its forelegs are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike.
pokemon.pokedexY: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile-it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sceptile has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This Pokémon raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

pokemon.name: Torchic
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if hugged.
pokemon.pokedexY: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Torchic sticks with its Trainer, following behind with unsteady steps. This Pokémon breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug-it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

pokemon.name: Combusken
pokemon.pokedexX: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp creis to intimidate foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon's legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out 10 kicks in one second.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This Pokémon's cry is very loud and distracting.

pokemon.name: Blaziken
pokemon.pokedexX: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs it jump clear over buildings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon's wrists burn.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs-it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon's blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

pokemon.name: Mudkip
pokemon.pokedexX: Its large tail fin propels it through water with powerful acceleration. It is strong in spite of its size.
pokemon.pokedexY: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The fin on Mudkip's head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In water, Mudkip breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this Pokémon will unleash its amazing power-it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

pokemon.name: Marshtomp
pokemon.pokedexX: It is at its best when on muddy ground with poor footing. It quickly overwhelms foes struggling in mud.
pokemon.pokedexY: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The surface of Marshtomp's body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Marshtomp is much faster at traveling through mud than it is at swimming. This Pokémon's hindquarters exhibit obvious development, giving it the ability to walk on just its hind legs.

pokemon.name: Swampert
pokemon.pokedexX: Its arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down its foe. It makes its nest on beautiful beaches.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swampert predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

pokemon.name: Poochyena
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.
pokemon.pokedexOR: At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Poochyena is an omnivore-it will eat anything. A distinguishing feature is how large its fangs are compared to its body. This Pokémon tries to intimidate its foes by making the hair on its tail bristle out.

pokemon.name: Mightyena
pokemon.pokedexX: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.
pokemon.pokedexY: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mightyena travel and act as a pack in the wild. The memory of its life in the wild compels the Pokémon to obey only those Trainers that it recognizes to possess superior skill.

pokemon.name: Zigzagoon
pokemon.pokedexX: It walks in zigzag fashion. It's good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
pokemon.pokedexY: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Zigzagoon restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This Pokémon does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The hair on Zigzagoon's back is bristly. It rubs the hard back hair against trees to leave its territorial markings. This Pokémon may play dead to fool foes in battle.

pokemon.name: Linoone
pokemon.pokedexX: When running in a straight line, it can easily top 60 miles an hour. It has a tough time with curved roads.
pokemon.pokedexY: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Linoone always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This Pokémon is very challenged by gently curving roads.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When hunting, Linoone will make a beeline straight for the prey at a full run. While this Pokémon is capable of topping 60 mph, it has to come to a screeching halt before it can turn.

pokemon.name: Wurmple
pokemon.pokedexX: It loves to eat leaves. If it is attacked by a Starly, it will defend itself with its spiked rear.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon's feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wurmple is targeted by Swellow as prey. This Pokémon will try to resist by pointing the spikes on its rear at the attacking predator. It will weaken the foe by leaking poison from the spikes.

pokemon.name: Silcoon
pokemon.pokedexX: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.
pokemon.pokedexY: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Silcoon was thought to endure hunger and not consume anything before its evolution. However, it is now thought that this Pokémon slakes its thirst by drinking rainwater that collects on its silk.

pokemon.name: Beautifly
pokemon.pokedexX: Vibrantly patterned wings are its prominent feature. It sucks sweet flower nectar with its long mouth.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Beautifly's favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Beautifly has a long mouth like a coiled needle, which is very convenient for collecting pollen from flowers. This Pokémon rides the spring winds as it flits around gathering pollen.

pokemon.name: Cascoon
pokemon.pokedexX: Its body, which is made of soft silk, hardens over time. When cracks appear, evolution is near.
pokemon.pokedexY: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If it is attacked, Cascoon remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This Pokémon will also not forget the pain it endured.

pokemon.name: Dustox
pokemon.pokedexX: A nocturnal Pokémon. Drawn by streetlights, they messily eat the leaves of trees lining boulevards.
pokemon.pokedexY: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Dustox flaps its wings, a fine dust is scattered all over. This dust is actually a powerful poison that will even make a pro wrestler sick. This Pokémon searches for food using its antennae like radar.

pokemon.name: Lotad
pokemon.pokedexX: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can't swim.
pokemon.pokedexY: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lotad live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this Pokémon travels on land in search of clean water.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lotad is said to have dwelled on land before. However, this Pokémon is thought to have returned to water because the leaf on its head grew large and heavy. It now lives by floating atop the water.

pokemon.name: Lombre
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives at the water's edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water-grass by day and becomes active at night.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler,  it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lombre is nocturnal-it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief maker. When this Pokémon spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lombre's entire body is covered by a slippery, slimy film. It feels horribly unpleasant to be touched by this Pokémon's hands. Lombre is often mistaken for a human child.

pokemon.name: Ludicolo
pokemon.pokedexX: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.
pokemon.pokedexY: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates  Ludicolo's cells, making it more powerful.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ludicolo begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This Pokémon is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Upon hearing an upbeat and cheerful rhythm, the cells in Ludicolo's body become very energetic and active. Even in battle, this Pokémon will exhibit an amazing amount of power.

pokemon.name: Seedot
pokemon.pokedexX: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Seedot attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this Pokémon's body becomes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Seedot looks exactly like an acorn when it is dangling from a tree branch. It startles other Pokémon by suddenly moving. This Pokémon polishes its body once a day using leaves.

pokemon.name: Nuzleaf
pokemon.pokedexX: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Nuzleaf live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This Pokémon dislikes having its long nose pinched.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon pulls out the leaf on its head and makes a flute with it. The sound of Nuzleaf's flute strikes fear and uncertainty in the hearts of people lost in a forest.

pokemon.name: Shiftry
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.
pokemon.pokedexY: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Shiftry is a mysterious Pokémon that is said to live atop towering trees dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Shiftry's large fans generate awesome gusts of wind at a speed close to 100 feet per second. The whipped-up wind blows anything away. This Pokémon chooses to live quietly deep in forests.

pokemon.name: Taillow
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.
pokemon.pokedexY: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Taillow is young-it has only just left its nest. As a result, it sometimes becomes lonesome and cries at night. This Pokémon feeds on Wurmple that live in forests.

pokemon.name: Swellow
pokemon.pokedexX: If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.
pokemon.pokedexY: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow's clawed feet, preventing escape.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swellow is very conscientious about the upkeep of its glossy wings. Once two Swellow are gathered, they diligently take care of cleaning each other's wings.

pokemon.name: Wingull
pokemon.pokedexX: Catching sea winds with its long wings, it soars as if it were a glider. It folds its wings to rest.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs.  Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Wingull has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This Pokémon rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wingull rides updrafts rising from the sea by extending its long and narrow wings to glide. This Pokémon's long beak is useful for catching prey.

pokemon.name: Pelipper
pokemon.pokedexX: It dips its large bill in the sea, then scoops up numerous prey along with water.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small  Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Pelipper is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon and eggs inside its massive bill. This Pokémon builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Pelipper searches for food while in flight by skimming the wave tops. This Pokémon dips its large bill in the sea to scoop up food, then swallows everything in one big gulp.

pokemon.name: Ralts
pokemon.pokedexX: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or  Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and  Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ralts has the ability to sense the emotions of people. If its Trainer is in a cheerful mood, this Pokémon grows cheerful and joyous in the same way.

pokemon.name: Kirlia
pokemon.pokedexX: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for  its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances  when happy.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the  space around it and see into the future.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its Trainer grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kirlia uses the horns on its head to amplify its psychokinetic power. When the Pokémon uses its power, the air around it becomes distorted, creating mirages of nonexistent scenery.

pokemon.name: Gardevoir
pokemon.pokedexX: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Gardevoir has the psychokinetic power to distort the dimensions and create a small black hole. This Pokémon will try to protect its Trainer even at the risk of its own life.

pokemon.name: Surskit
pokemon.pokedexX: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.
pokemon.pokedexY: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.
pokemon.pokedexOR: From the tips of its feet, Surskit secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If Surskit senses danger, it secretes a thick, sugary syrup from the tip of its head. There are some Pokémon that love eating this syrup.

pokemon.name: Masquerain
pokemon.pokedexX: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This Pokémon flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction-even sideways and backwards-as if it were a helicopter.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Masquerain's antennas have eyelike patterns that usually give it an angry look. If the "eyes" are droopy and appear sad, it is said to be a sign that a heavy rainfall is on its way.

pokemon.name: Shroomish
pokemon.pokedexX: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.
pokemon.pokedexY: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If Shroomish senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters spores from the top of its head. This Pokémon's spores are so toxic, they make trees and weeds wilt.

pokemon.name: Breloom
pokemon.pokedexX: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.
pokemon.pokedexY: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon's fighting technique puts boxers to shame.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The seeds ringing Breloom's tail are made of hardened toxic spores. It is horrible to eat the seeds. Just taking a bite of this Pokémon's seed will cause your stomach to rumble.

pokemon.name: Slakoth
pokemon.pokedexX: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it eats just three leaves a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Slakoth lolls around for over 20 hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon's sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Slakoth's heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.

pokemon.name: Vigoroth
pokemon.pokedexX: Its hearbeat is fast and its blood so agitated that it can't sit still for one secodn.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can't tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This Pokémon's stress level rises if it can't be moving constantly.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Vigoroth is simply incapable of remaining still. Even when it tries to sleep, the blood in its veins grows agitated, compelling this Pokémon to run wild throughout the jungle before it can settle down.

pokemon.name: Slaking
pokemon.pokedexX: The world's laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is the world's most slothful Pokémon However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wherever Slaking live, rings of over a yard in diameter appear in grassy fields. They are made by the Pokémon as it eats all the grass within reach while lying prone on the ground.

pokemon.name: Nincada
pokemon.pokedexX: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This Pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Nincada lives underground. It uses its sharp claws to carve the roots of trees and absorb moisture and nutrients. This Pokémon can't withstand bright sunlight so avoids it.

pokemon.name: Ninjask
pokemon.pokedexX: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.
pokemon.pokedexY: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes  unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this Pokémon was long believed to be invisible.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If Ninjask is not trained properly, it will refuse to obey the Trainer and cry loudly continuously. Because of this quality, this Pokémon is said to be one that puts the Trainer's abilities to the test.

pokemon.name: Shedinja
pokemon.pokedexX: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.
pokemon.pokedexY: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Shedinja's hard body doesn't move-not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this Pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Shedinja is a peculiar Pokémon. It seems to appear unsought in a Poké Ball after a Nincada evolves. This bizarre Pokémon is entirely immobile-it doesn't even breathe.

pokemon.name: Whismur
pokemon.pokedexX: It usually murmurs but starts crying loudly if it senses danger. It stops when its ear covers are shut.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Normally, Whismur's voice is very quiet-it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this Pokémon senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Whismur is very timid. If it starts to cry loudly, it becomes startled by its own crying and cries even harder. When it finally stops crying, the Pokémon goes to sleep, all tired out.

pokemon.name: Loudred
pokemon.pokedexX: It shouts loudly by inhaling air, and then uses its well-developed stomach muscles to exhale.
pokemon.pokedexY: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Loudred's bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This Pokémon's round ears serve as loudspeakers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Loudred shouts while stamping its feet. After it finishes shouting, this Pokémon becomes incapable of hearing anything for a while. This is considered to be a weak point.

pokemon.name: Exploud
pokemon.pokedexX: It howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor--or like an earthquake has struck.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Exploud triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this Pokémon violently inhales from the ports on its body, it's a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Exploud communicates its feelings to the others by emitting whistle-like sounds from the tubes on its body. This Pokémon only raises its voice when it is in battle.

pokemon.name: Makuhita
pokemon.pokedexX: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.
pokemon.pokedexY: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Makuhita is tenacious-it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this Pokémon stores more energy in its body for evolving.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Makuhita has a tireless spirit-it will never give up hope. It eats a lot of food, gets plenty of sleep, and it trains very rigorously. By living that way, this Pokémon packs its body with energy.

pokemon.name: Hariyama
pokemon.pokedexX: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.
pokemon.pokedexY: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Hariyama practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this Pokémon's powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Hariyama's thick body may appear fat, but it is actually a hunk of solid muscle. If this Pokémon bears down and tightens all its muscles, its body becomes as hard as a rock.

pokemon.name: Azurill
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon that lives by water. It moves quickly on land by bouncing on its big tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: It swings its large, nutrient-filled tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Azurill spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these Pokémon managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Azurill's tail is large and bouncy. It is packed full of the nutrients this Pokémon needs to grow. Azurill can be seen bouncing and playing on its big, rubbery tail.

pokemon.name: Nosepass
pokemon.pokedexX: Its magnetic nose always faces north and draws iron objects to its body to protect itself better.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north.  Travellers check Nosepass to get their bearings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Nosepass's magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these Pokémon meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Nosepass had been said to be completely unmoving, with its magnetic nose pointed due north. However, close observation has revealed that the Pokémon actually moves by a little over 3/8 of an inch every year.

pokemon.name: Skitty
pokemon.pokedexX: It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Skitty is known to chase around playfully after its own tail. In the wild, this Pokémon lives in holes in the trees of forests. It is very popular as a pet because of its adorable looks.

pokemon.name: Delcatty
pokemon.pokedexX: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Delcatty sleeps anywhere it wants without keeping a permanent nest. If other Pokémon approach it as it sleeps, this Pokémon will never fight-it will just move away somewhere else.

pokemon.name: Sableye
pokemon.pokedexX: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.
pokemon.pokedexY: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sableye lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these Pokémon are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sableye digs the ground with sharpened claws to find rocks that it eats. Substances in the eaten rocks crystallize and rise up to the Pokémon's body surface.

pokemon.name: Mawile
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.
pokemon.pokedexY: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Don't be taken in by this Pokémon's cute face-it's very dangerous. Mawile fools the foe into letting down its guard, then chomps down with its massive jaws. The steel jaws are really horns that have been transformed.

pokemon.name: Aron
pokemon.pokedexX: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that  covered its whole body and develops a new one.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon has a body of steel. To make its body, Aron feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Aron has a body of steel. With one all-out charge, this Pokémon can demolish even a heavy dump truck. The destroyed dump truck then becomes a handy meal for the Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Lairon
pokemon.pokedexX: It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.
pokemon.pokedexY: It habitually shows off its strength with the size of  sparks it creates by ramming its steel body  into boulders.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This Pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lairon feeds on iron contained in rocks and water. It makes its nest on mountains where iron ore is buried. As a result, the Pokémon often clashes with humans mining the iron ore.

pokemon.name: Aggron
pokemon.pokedexX: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don't take it lightly.
pokemon.pokedexY: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by  breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Aggron claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This Pokémon vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Aggron is protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this Pokémon will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

pokemon.name: Meditite
pokemon.pokedexX: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.
pokemon.pokedexY: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Meditite heightens its inner energy through meditation. It survives on just one berry a day. Minimal eating is another aspect of this Pokémon's training.

pokemon.name: Medicham
pokemon.pokedexX: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the  same motion.
pokemon.pokedexY: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Through the power of meditation, Medicham developed its sixth sense. It gained the ability to use psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon is known to meditate for a whole month without eating.

pokemon.name: Electrike
pokemon.pokedexX: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Electrike stores electricity in its long body hair. This Pokémon stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Electrike runs faster than the human eye can follow. The friction from running is converted into electricity, which is then stored in this Pokémon's fur.

pokemon.name: Manectric
pokemon.pokedexX: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.
pokemon.pokedexY: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Manectric discharges strong electricity from its mane. The mane is used for collecting electricity in the atmosphere. This Pokémon creates thunderclouds above its head.

pokemon.name: Plusle
pokemon.pokedexX: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
pokemon.pokedexY: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts  out its body to create crackling noises.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Plusle always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this Pokémon shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Plusle is cheering on its partner, it flashes with electric sparks from all over its body. If its partner loses, this Pokémon cries loudly.

pokemon.name: Minun
pokemon.pokedexX: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.
pokemon.pokedexY: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Minun loves to cheer on its partner in battle. It gives off sparks from its body while it is doing so. If its partner is in trouble, this Pokémon gives off increasing amounts of sparks.

pokemon.name: Volbeat
pokemon.pokedexX: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise's sweet aroma.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.
pokemon.pokedexOR: With the arrival of night, Volbeat emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This Pokémon is attracted by the sweet aroma of Illumise.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Volbeat's tail glows like a lightbulb. With other Volbeat, it uses its tail to draw geometric shapes in the night sky. This Pokémon loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

pokemon.name: Illumise
pokemon.pokedexX: Its fragrance attracts a swarm of Volbeat, so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.
pokemon.pokedexY: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Illumise attracts a swarm of Volbeat using a sweet fragrance. Once the Volbeat have gathered, this Pokémon leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Illumise leads a flight of illuminated Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. This Pokémon is said to earn greater respect from its peers by composing more complex designs in the sky.

pokemon.name: Roselia
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.
pokemon.pokedexY: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this Pokémon brings serenity to living things.
pokemon.pokedexAS: On extremely rare occasions, a Roselia is said to appear with its flowers in unusual colors. The thorns on this Pokémon's head contain a vicious poison.

pokemon.name: Gulpin
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
pokemon.pokedexY: There is nothing its stomach can't digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Virtually all of Gulpin's body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This Pokémon's stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Most of Gulpin's body is made up of its stomach-its heart and brain are very small in comparison. This Pokémon's stomach contains special enzymes that dissolve anything.

pokemon.name: Swalot
pokemon.pokedexX: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When Swalot spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this Pokémon gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swalot has no teeth, so what it eats, it swallows whole, no matter what. Its cavernous mouth yawns widely. An automobile tire could easily fit inside this Pokémon's mouth.

pokemon.name: Carvanha
pokemon.pokedexX: They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives in massive rivers that course through jungles. It swarms prey that enter its territory.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Carvanha's strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If anything invades Carvanha's territory, it will swarm and tear at the intruder with its pointed fangs. On its own, however, this Pokémon turns suddenly timid.

pokemon.name: Sharpedo
pokemon.pokedexX: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."
pokemon.pokedexY: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Nicknamed "the bully of the sea," Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This Pokémon's drawback is its inability to swim long distances.

pokemon.name: Wailmer
pokemon.pokedexX: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.
pokemon.pokedexY: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Wailmer's nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wailmer can store water inside its body to transform itself into a ball for bouncing around on the ground. By filling itself up with more water, this Pokémon can elevate the height of its bounces.

pokemon.name: Wailord
pokemon.pokedexX: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.
pokemon.pokedexY: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Wailord is the largest of all identified Pokémon up to now. This giant Pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When chasing prey, Wailord herds them by leaping out of the water and making a humongous splash. It is breathtaking to see this Pokémon leaping out of the sea with others in its pod.

pokemon.name: Numel
pokemon.pokedexX: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.
pokemon.pokedexY: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Numel is extremely dull witted-it doesn't notice being hit. However, it can't stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon's body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Numel stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the Pokémon's body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

pokemon.name: Camerupt
pokemon.pokedexX: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.
pokemon.pokedexY: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The humps on Camerupt's back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokémon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

pokemon.name: Torkoal
pokemon.pokedexX: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.
pokemon.pokedexY: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Torkoal digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this Pokémon spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Torkoal generates energy by burning coal. It grows weaker as the fire dies down. When it is preparing for battle, this Pokémon burns more coal.

pokemon.name: Spoink
pokemon.pokedexX: It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.
pokemon.pokedexY: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Spoink bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this Pokémon cannot afford to stop bouncing-if it stops, its heart will stop.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Spoink keeps a pearl on top of its head. The pearl functions to amplify this Pokémon's psychokinetic powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger pearl.

pokemon.name: Grumpig
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes' minds.
pokemon.pokedexY: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this Pokémon uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to wield its fantastic powers. When it is doing so, it dances bizarrely. This Pokémon's black pearls are valuable as works of art.

pokemon.name: Spinda
pokemon.pokedexX: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot  patterns is less than one in four billion.
pokemon.pokedexOR: All the Spinda that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this Pokémon give it the appearance of dancing.
pokemon.pokedexAS: No two Spinda are said to have identical spot patterns on their hides. This Pokémon moves in a curious manner as if it is stumbling in dizziness. Its lurching movements can cause the opponent to become confused.

pokemon.name: Trapinch
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in arid deserts. It makes a sloping pit trap in sand where it patiently awaits prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Trapinch's nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. This Pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Trapinch is a patient hunter. It digs an inescapable pit in a desert and waits for its prey to come tumbling down. This Pokémon can go a whole week without access to any water.

pokemon.name: Vibrava
pokemon.pokedexX: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.
pokemon.pokedexY: It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping  its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the  prey with acid.
pokemon.pokedexOR: To make prey faint, Vibrava generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This Pokémon's ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Vibrava's wings have not yet completed the process of growing. Rather than flying long distances, they are more useful for generating ultrasonic waves by vibrating.

pokemon.name: Flygon
pokemon.pokedexX: It hides itself by kicking up desert sand with its wings. Red covers shield its eyes from sand.
pokemon.pokedexY: Known as "The Desert Spirit," this Pokémon hides in  the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Flygon is nicknamed "the elemental spirit of the desert." Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this Pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Flygon whips up a sandstorm by flapping its wings. The wings create a series of notes that sound like singing. Because the "singing" is the only thing that can be heard in a sandstorm, this Pokémon is said to be the desert spirit.

pokemon.name: Cacnea
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.
pokemon.pokedexY: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower Cacnea grows. This Pokémon battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

pokemon.name: Cacturne
pokemon.pokedexX: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day's desert heat.
pokemon.pokedexY: Packs of them follow travellers through the desert until the travellers can no longer move.
pokemon.pokedexOR: During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If a traveler is going through a desert in the thick of night, Cacturne will follow in a ragtag group. The Pokémon are biding their time, waiting for the traveler to tire and become incapable of moving.

pokemon.name: Swablu
pokemon.pokedexX: For some reason, it likes to land on people's heads softly and act like it's a hat.
pokemon.pokedexY: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes  a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Swablu has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This Pokémon is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swablu loves to make things clean. If it spots something dirty, it will wipe and polish it with its cottony wings. If its wings become dirty, this Pokémon finds a stream and showers itself.

pokemon.name: Altaria
pokemon.pokedexX: It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you're in a dream.
pokemon.pokedexY: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and  blends into the clouds. It sings in a  beautiful soprano.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this Pokémon makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokémon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

pokemon.name: Zangoose
pokemon.pokedexX: It has feuded with Seviper for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Memories of battling its archrival Seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose's body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Zangoose usually stays on all fours, but when angered, it gets up on its hind legs and extends its claws. This Pokémon shares a bitter rivalry with Seviper that dates back over generations.

pokemon.name: Seviper
pokemon.pokedexX: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any  Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Seviper's swordlike tail serves two purposes-it slashes foes and douses them with secreted poison. This Pokémon will not give up its long-running blood feud with Zangoose.

pokemon.name: Lunatone
pokemon.pokedexX: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.
pokemon.pokedexY: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteoroid fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lunatone becomes active around the time of the full moon. Instead of walking, it moves by floating in midair. The Pokémon's intimidating red eyes cause all those who see it to become transfixed with fear.

pokemon.name: Solrock
pokemon.pokedexX: Solar energy is the source of its power,  so it is strong during the daytime.  When it spins, its body shines.
pokemon.pokedexY: It absorbs solar energy during the day. Always expressionless, it can sense what its foe is thinking.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Solrock is a new species of Pokémon that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this Pokémon releases intensely bright light.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sunlight is the source of Solrock's power. It is said to possess the ability to read the emotions of others. This Pokémon gives off intense heat while rotating its body.

pokemon.name: Barboach
pokemon.pokedexX: It coats its entire body with a slimy fluid so it can squirm and slip away if grabbed.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its whiskers make a superb radar. They are used to  locate prey, even in the murkiest of water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Barboach's sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Barboach's body is covered with a slimy film. If a foe grabs it, this Pokémon just slips out of the enemy's grip. This Pokémon grows weak if the slimy coating dries up.

pokemon.name: Whiscash
pokemon.pokedexX: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it, it sets off tremors by thrashing around.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps.  It will eat anything--if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Whiscash is extremely territorial. Just one of these Pokémon will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If Whiscash goes on a wild rampage, it sets off a quake-like tremor with a radius of over three miles. This Pokémon has the ability to predict real earthquakes.

pokemon.name: Corphish
pokemon.pokedexX: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Corphish were originally foreign Pokémon that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This Pokémon is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Corphish catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food-it will eat anything. This Pokémon has no trouble living in filthy water.

pokemon.name: Crawdaunt
pokemon.pokedexX: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.
pokemon.pokedexY: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this Pokémon, making them desolate places.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Crawdaunt molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this Pokémon hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.

pokemon.name: Baltoy
pokemon.pokedexX: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.
pokemon.pokedexY: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some BALTOY have been seen spinning on their heads.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this Pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As soon as it spots others of its kind, Baltoy congregates with them and then begins crying noisily in unison. This Pokémon sleeps while cleverly balancing itself on its one foot.

pokemon.name: Claydol
pokemon.pokedexX: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This Pokémon moves about while levitating.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Claydol is an enigma that appeared from a clay statue made by an ancient civilization dating back 20,000 years. This Pokémon shoots beams from both its hands.

pokemon.name: Lileep
pokemon.pokedexX: It disguises its tentacles as flowers to attract and catch prey. It became extinct in ancient times.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lileep became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient Pokémon attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles shaped like flower petals.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lileep is an ancient Pokémon that was regenerated from a fossil. It remains permanently anchored to a rock. From its immobile perch, this Pokémon intently scans for prey with its two eyes.

pokemon.name: Cradily
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.
pokemon.pokedexY: It ensnares prey with its eight tentacles. It then melts the prey with a strong acid before feeding.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This Pokémon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Cradily's body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This Pokémon secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.

pokemon.name: Anorith
pokemon.pokedexX: It is a kind of Pokémon progenitor. It uses its extending claws to catch prey hiding among rocks on the seafloor.
pokemon.pokedexY: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive Pokémon once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Anorith is said to be a type of Pokémon predecessor, with eight wings at the sides of its body. This Pokémon swam in the primordial sea by undulating these eight wings.

pokemon.name: Armaldo
pokemon.pokedexX: Its enormous, retractable claws can cut through most anything. Its entire body is clad in sturdy plates.
pokemon.pokedexY: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Armaldo's tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This Pokémon's two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Armaldo is a Pokémon species that became extinct in prehistoric times. This Pokémon is said to have walked on its hind legs, which would have been more convenient for life on land.

pokemon.name: Feebas
pokemon.pokedexX: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Feebas's fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokémon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: While Feebas's body is in tatters, it has a hardy and tenacious life force that enables it to live anywhere. However, this Pokémon is also slow and dimwitted, making it an easy catch.

pokemon.name: Milotic
pokemon.pokedexX: Milotic is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is the world's most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokémon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Milotic live at the bottom of large lakes. When this Pokémon's body glows a vivid pink, it releases a pulsing wave of energy that brings soothing calm to troubled hearts.

pokemon.name: Castform
