pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon can change its cells, taking different forms based on the temperature and humidity.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud, depending on the weather.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Castform borrows the power of nature to transform itself into the guises of the sun, rain, and snow-clouds. This Pokémon's feelings change with the weather.

pokemon.name: Kecleon
pokemon.pokedexX: It can freely change its body's color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn't change, however.
pokemon.pokedexY: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Kecleon is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception-this Pokémon can't change the zigzag pattern on its belly.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kecleon alters its body coloration to blend in with its surroundings, allowing it to sneak up on its prey unnoticed. Then it lashes out with its long, stretchy tongue to instantly ensnare the unsuspecting target.

pokemon.name: Shuppet
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice-- or so it's said. It's very active at night.
pokemon.pokedexY: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Shuppet is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this Pokémon will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person's home.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Shuppet grows by feeding on dark emotions, such as vengefulness and envy, in the hearts of people. It roams through cities in search of grudges that taint people.

pokemon.name: Banette
pokemon.pokedexX: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.
pokemon.pokedexY: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokémon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A cursed energy permeated the stuffing of a discarded and forgotten plush doll, giving it new life as Banette. The Pokémon's energy would escape if it were to ever open its mouth.

pokemon.name: Duskull
pokemon.pokedexX: It doggedly pursues its prey wherever it goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away--or so it's said.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Duskull wanders lost among the deep darkness of midnight. There is an oft-told admonishment given to misbehaving children that this Pokémon will spirit away bad children who earn scoldings from their mothers.

pokemon.name: Dusclops
pokemon.pokedexX: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is hollow. It is said that those who look into its body are sucked into the void.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Dusclops's body is completely hollow-there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This Pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Dusclops absorbs anything, however large the object may be. This Pokémon hypnotizes its foe by waving its hands in a macabre manner and by bringing its single eye to bear. The hypnotized foe is made to do Dusclops's bidding.

pokemon.name: Tropius
pokemon.pokedexX: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.
pokemon.pokedexY: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The bunches of fruit around Tropius's neck are very popular with children. This Pokémon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokémon flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.

pokemon.name: Chimecho
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.
pokemon.pokedexY: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In high winds, Chimecho cries as it hangs from a tree branch or the eaves of a building using a suction cup on its head. This Pokémon plucks berries with its long tail and eats them.

pokemon.name: Absol
pokemon.pokedexX: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.
pokemon.pokedexY: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Absol has the ability to foretell the coming of natural disasters. It lives in a harsh, rugged mountain environment. This Pokémon very rarely ventures down from the mountains.

pokemon.name: Wynaut
pokemon.pokedexX: It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.
pokemon.pokedexY: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Wynaut can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this Pokémon will be slapping the ground with its tail.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Wynaut gather on moonlit nights to play by squeezing up against each other. By being squeezed, this Pokémon gains endurance and is trained to dole out powerful counterattacks.

pokemon.name: Snorunt
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.
pokemon.pokedexY: In the snow country, certain folklore says a house will prosper if a Snorunt lives there.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Snorunt live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this Pokémon steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Snorunt survives by eating only snow and ice. Old folklore claims that a house visited by this Pokémon is sure to prosper for many generations to come.

pokemon.name: Glalie
pokemon.pokedexX: To protect itself, it clad its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Glalie has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its prey solid. After immobilizing its prey in ice, this Pokémon enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.

pokemon.name: Spheal
pokemon.pokedexX: They can't swim well yet, and they move much faster by rolling. When they're happy, they clap fins.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Spheal is much faster rolling than walking to get around. When groups of this Pokémon eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Spheal always travels by rolling around on its ball-like body. When the season for ice floes arrives, this Pokémon can be seen rolling about on ice and crossing the sea.

pokemon.name: Sealeo
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a very sensitive nose. It touches new things with its nose to examine them.
pokemon.pokedexY: Be it Spheal or Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a Spheal on its nose.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sealeo often balances and rolls things on the tip of its nose. While the Pokémon is rolling something, it checks the object's aroma and texture to determine whether it likes the object or not.

pokemon.name: Walrein
pokemon.pokedexX: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.
pokemon.pokedexY: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Walrein's two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing 10 tons with one blow. This Pokémon's thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Walrein swims all over in frigid seawater while crushing icebergs with its grand, imposing tusks. Its thick layer of blubber makes enemy attacks bounce off harmlessly.

pokemon.name: Clamperl
pokemon.pokedexX: When it evolves, it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it's held.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Clamperl's sturdy shell is not only good for protection-it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown Clamperl's shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Clamperl grows while being protected by its rock-hard shell. When its body becomes too large to fit inside the shell, it is sure evidence that this Pokémon is getting close to evolution.

pokemon.name: Huntail
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives deep in the sea where no light ever filters down. It lights up its small fishlike tail to attract prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Huntail's presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This Pokémon's eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Huntail's tail is shaped like a fish. It uses the tail to attract prey, then swallows the prey whole with its large, gaping mouth. This Pokémon swims by wiggling its slender body like a snake.

pokemon.name: Gorebyss
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Gorebyss lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this Pokémon's body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Although Gorebyss is the very picture of elegance and beauty while swimming, it is also cruel. When it spots prey, this Pokémon inserts its thin mouth into the prey's body and drains the prey of its body fluids.

pokemon.name: Relicanth
pokemon.pokedexX: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.
pokemon.pokedexY: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea  exploration. It has not changed in over  100 million years.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Relicanth is a Pokémon species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Relicanth is a rare species that was discovered in deep-sea explorations. This Pokémon's body withstands the enormous water pressure of the ocean depths. Its body is covered in tough scales that are like craggy rocks.

pokemon.name: Luvdisc
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.
pokemon.pokedexY: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pokémon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean's waves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Luvdisc's heart-shaped body is a symbol of love and romance. It is said that any couple meeting this Pokémon is promised a loving relationship that never ends.

pokemon.name: Bagon
pokemon.pokedexX: Its well-developed neck muscles and iron-like head can smash boulders into pieces.
pokemon.pokedexY: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Bagon has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this Pokémon hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Bagon harbors a never-ending dream of one day soaring high among the clouds. As if trying to dispel its frustration over its inability to fly, this Pokémon slams its hard head against huge rocks and shatters them into pebbles.

pokemon.name: Shelgon
pokemon.pokedexX: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Inside Shelgon's armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This Pokémon's shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Covering Shelgon's body are outgrowths much like bones. The shell is very hard and bounces off enemy attacks. When awaiting evolution, this Pokémon hides away in a cavern.

pokemon.name: Salamence
pokemon.pokedexX: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.
pokemon.pokedexY: It's uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Salamence came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this Pokémon's cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By evolving into Salamence, this Pokémon finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Beldum
pokemon.pokedexX: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism, letting it float.
pokemon.pokedexY: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout Beldum's body. This Pokémon communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Beldum keeps itself floating by generating a magnetic force that repels earth's natural magnetism. When it sleeps, this Pokémon anchors itself to a cliff using the hooks on its rear.

pokemon.name: Metang
pokemon.pokedexX: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won't be scratched if it collides with a jet.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this Pokémon generates strong psychokinetic power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. This Pokémon turns its arms to the rear for traveling at high speed.

pokemon.name: Metagross
pokemon.pokedexX: With four linked brains, it's more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokémon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Metagross is the result of two Metang achieving fusion. When hunting, this Pokémon pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large mouth on its stomach.

pokemon.name: Regirock
pokemon.pokedexX: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.
pokemon.pokedexY: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Regirock was sealed away by people long ago. If this Pokémon's body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Regirock's body is composed entirely of rocks. Recently, a study made the startling discovery that the rocks were all unearthed from different locations.

pokemon.name: Regice
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can't be melted, even by magma.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Regice's body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can't be melted, even by fire. This Pokémon controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Regice cloaks itself with frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit. Things will freeze solid just by going near this Pokémon. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.

pokemon.name: Registeel
pokemon.pokedexX: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Registeel has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this Pokémon eats.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Registeel was imprisoned by people in ancient times. The metal composing its body is thought to be a curious substance that is not of this earth.

pokemon.name: Latias
pokemon.pokedexX: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

pokemon.name: Latios
pokemon.pokedexX: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

pokemon.name: Kyogre
pokemon.pokedexX: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

pokemon.name: Groudon
pokemon.pokedexX: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre
pokemon.pokedexY: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

pokemon.name: Rayquaza
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

pokemon.name: Jirachi
pokemon.pokedexX: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

pokemon.name: Deoxys
pokemon.pokedexX: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon’s chest appears to be its brain.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

pokemon.name: Turtwig
pokemon.pokedexX: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.
pokemon.pokedexY: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

pokemon.name: Grotle
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
pokemon.pokedexY: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

pokemon.name: Torterra
pokemon.pokedexX: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.
pokemon.pokedexY: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

pokemon.name: Chimchar
pokemon.pokedexX: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.
pokemon.pokedexY: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

pokemon.name: Monferno
pokemon.pokedexX: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.
pokemon.pokedexY: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

pokemon.name: Infernape
pokemon.pokedexX: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.
pokemon.pokedexY: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

pokemon.name: Piplup
pokemon.pokedexX: It doesn't like to be taken care of. It's difficult to bond with since it won't listen to its Trainer.
pokemon.pokedexY: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It doesn't like to be taken care of. It's difficult to bond with since it won't listen to its Trainer.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

pokemon.name: Prinplup
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

pokemon.name: Empoleon
pokemon.pokedexX: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.
pokemon.pokedexY: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

pokemon.name: Starly
pokemon.pokedexX: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
pokemon.pokedexY: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

pokemon.name: Staravia
pokemon.pokedexX: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

pokemon.name: Staraptor
pokemon.pokedexX: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

pokemon.name: Bidoof
pokemon.pokedexX: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
pokemon.pokedexY: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

pokemon.name: Bibarel
pokemon.pokedexX: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.
pokemon.pokedexY: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

pokemon.name: Kricketot
pokemon.pokedexX: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.
pokemon.pokedexY: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

pokemon.name: Kricketune
pokemon.pokedexX: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.
pokemon.pokedexY: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

pokemon.name: Shinx
pokemon.pokedexX: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.
pokemon.pokedexY: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.
pokemon.pokedexAS: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

pokemon.name: Luxio
pokemon.pokedexX: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.
pokemon.pokedexY: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

pokemon.name: Luxray
pokemon.pokedexX: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey--even those taking shelter behind a wall.
pokemon.pokedexY: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey-even those taking shelter behind a wall.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

pokemon.name: Budew
pokemon.pokedexX: When it feels the sun's warm touch, it opens its bud  to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.
pokemon.pokedexY: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When it feels the sun's warm touch, it opens its bud to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

pokemon.name: Roserade
pokemon.pokedexX: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.
pokemon.pokedexAS: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

pokemon.name: Cranidos
pokemon.pokedexX: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its headbutts.
pokemon.pokedexY: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its headbutts.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

pokemon.name: Rampardos
pokemon.pokedexX: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As a result, its brain never gets the chance to grow.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its skull is a hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As a result, its brain never gets the chance to grow.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

pokemon.name: Shieldon
pokemon.pokedexX: It habitually polishes its face by rubbing it against tree trunks. It is weak to attacks from behind.
pokemon.pokedexY: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It habitually polishes its face by rubbing it against tree trunks. It is weak to attacks from behind.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

pokemon.name: Bastiodon
pokemon.pokedexX: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.
pokemon.pokedexY: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

pokemon.name: Burmy
pokemon.pokedexX: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
pokemon.pokedexY: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.
pokemon.pokedexOR: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

pokemon.name: Wormadam-Plant
pokemon.pokedexX: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.
pokemon.pokedexY: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

pokemon.name: Mothim
pokemon.pokedexX: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

pokemon.name: Combee
pokemon.pokedexX: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers  honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.
pokemon.pokedexY: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

pokemon.name: Vespiquen
pokemon.pokedexX: It houses its colony in cels in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding
pokemon.pokedexY: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

pokemon.name: Pachirisu
pokemon.pokedexX: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.
pokemon.pokedexY: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

pokemon.name: Buizel
pokemon.pokedexX: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.
pokemon.pokedexY: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

pokemon.name: Floatzel
pokemon.pokedexX: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

pokemon.name: Cherubi
pokemon.pokedexX: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball is drained of nutrients, it shrivels to herald evolution.
pokemon.pokedexY: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball is drained of nutrients, it shrivels to herald evolution.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

pokemon.name: Cherrim
pokemon.pokedexX: During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms, its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.
pokemon.pokedexOR: During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms, its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

pokemon.name: Shellos
pokemon.pokedexX: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

pokemon.name: Gastrodon
pokemon.pokedexX: When its natural enemy attacks, it oozes purple fluid and escapes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When its natural enemy attacks, it oozes purple fluid and escapes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.

pokemon.name: Ambipom
pokemon.pokedexX: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.
pokemon.pokedexY: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.
pokemon.pokedexAS: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

pokemon.name: Drifloon
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and  Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.
pokemon.pokedexY: These Pokémon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.
pokemon.pokedexAS: These Pokémon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.

pokemon.name: Drifblim
pokemon.pokedexX: It carries people and Pokémon when it flies. But since it only drifts, it can end up anywhere.
pokemon.pokedexY: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It carries people and Pokémon when it flies. But since it only drifts, it can end up anywhere.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

pokemon.name: Buneary
pokemon.pokedexX: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

pokemon.name: Lopunny
pokemon.pokedexX: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
pokemon.pokedexY: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

pokemon.name: Mismagius
pokemon.pokedexX: It chants incantations. While they usually torment targets, some chants bring happiness.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It chants incantations. While they usually torment targets, some chants bring happiness.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

pokemon.name: Honchkrow
pokemon.pokedexX: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."
pokemon.pokedexY: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."
pokemon.pokedexAS: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

pokemon.name: Glameow
pokemon.pokedexX: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

pokemon.name: Purugly
pokemon.pokedexX: It would claim another Pokémon's nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.
pokemon.pokedexY: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It would claim another Pokémon's nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.
pokemon.pokedexAS: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

pokemon.name: Chingling
pokemon.pokedexX: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.
pokemon.pokedexY: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.
pokemon.pokedexAS: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

pokemon.name: Stunky
pokemon.pokedexX: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.
pokemon.pokedexY: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

pokemon.name: Skuntank
pokemon.pokedexX: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.
pokemon.pokedexY: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

pokemon.name: Bronzor
pokemon.pokedexX: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.
pokemon.pokedexY: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

pokemon.name: Bronzong
pokemon.pokedexX: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.
pokemon.pokedexY: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

pokemon.name: Bonsly
pokemon.pokedexX: It prefers arid environments. It leaks water from its eyes to adjust its body's fluid levels.
pokemon.pokedexY: It prefers and arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It prefers arid environments. It leaks water from its eyes to adjust its body's fluid levels.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

pokemon.name: Mime Jr.
pokemon.pokedexX: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy's movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!
pokemon.pokedexY: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy's movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!
pokemon.pokedexAS: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Happiny
pokemon.pokedexX: It carries a round, egg-shaped rock in its belly pouch and gives the rock to its friends.
pokemon.pokedexY: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It carries a round, egg-shaped rock in its belly pouch and gives the rock to its friends.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.

pokemon.name: Chatot
pokemon.pokedexX: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it's one of them. This way they won't attack  it.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it's one of them. This way they won't attack it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

pokemon.name: Spiritomb
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone
pokemon.pokedexY: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as  punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

pokemon.name: Gible
pokemon.pokedexX: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
pokemon.pokedexY: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

pokemon.name: Gabite
pokemon.pokedexX: It love sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
pokemon.pokedexY: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

pokemon.name: Garchomp
pokemon.pokedexX: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flies at speeds equals to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

pokemon.name: Munchlax
pokemon.pokedexX: It hides food under its long body hair. However, it forgets it has hidden the food.
pokemon.pokedexY: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It hides food under its long body hair. However, it forgets it has hidden the food.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

pokemon.name: Riolu
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses the shape of auras, which change according to emotion, to communicate with others.
pokemon.pokedexY: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It uses the shapes of auras, which change according to emotion, to communicate with others.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

pokemon.name: Lucario
pokemon.pokedexX: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.
pokemon.pokedexY: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

pokemon.name: Hippopotas
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration,  it expels grainy sand from its body.
pokemon.pokedexY: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

pokemon.name: Hippowdon
pokemon.pokedexX: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.
pokemon.pokedexY: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

pokemon.name: Skorupi
pokemon.pokedexX: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

pokemon.name: Drapion
pokemon.pokedexX: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

pokemon.name: Croagunk
pokemon.pokedexX: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.
pokemon.pokedexY: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

pokemon.name: Toxicroak
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

pokemon.name: Carnivine
pokemon.pokedexX: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

pokemon.name: Finneon
pokemon.pokedexX: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.
pokemon.pokedexY: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.
pokemon.pokedexAS: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

pokemon.name: Lumineon
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.
pokemon.pokedexY: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.
pokemon.pokedexAS: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

pokemon.name: Mantyke
pokemon.pokedexX: The pattern on its back varies by region. It often swims in a school of Remoraid.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The pattern on its back varies by region. It often swims in a school of Remoraid.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

pokemon.name: Snover
pokemon.pokedexX: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.
pokemon.pokedexY: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.
pokemon.pokedexOR: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

pokemon.name: Abomasnow
pokemon.pokedexX: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

pokemon.name: Weavile
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.
pokemon.pokedexY: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

pokemon.name: Magnezone
pokemon.pokedexX: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone is too strong, making them attract each other so they cannot move.
pokemon.pokedexY: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone is too strong, making them attract each other so they cannot move.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

pokemon.name: Lickilicky
pokemon.pokedexX: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
pokemon.pokedexY: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

pokemon.name: Rhyperior
pokemon.pokedexX: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.
pokemon.pokedexY: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.
pokemon.pokedexOR: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

pokemon.name: Tangrowth
pokemon.pokedexX: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

pokemon.name: Electivire
pokemon.pokedexX: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.
pokemon.pokedexY: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

pokemon.name: Magmortar
pokemon.pokedexX: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.
pokemon.pokedexY: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

pokemon.name: Togekiss
pokemon.pokedexX: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.
pokemon.pokedexY: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.
pokemon.pokedexOR: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

pokemon.name: Yanmega
pokemon.pokedexX: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes' heads instantly while flying at high speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

pokemon.name: Leafeon
pokemon.pokedexX: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you'll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.
pokemon.pokedexY: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you'll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

pokemon.name: Glaceon
pokemon.pokedexX: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

pokemon.name: Gliscor
pokemon.pokedexX: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!
pokemon.pokedexY: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

pokemon.name: Mamoswine
pokemon.pokedexX: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around a long, long, long time.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around a long, long, long time.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

pokemon.name: Porygon-Z
pokemon.pokedexX: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...
pokemon.pokedexOR: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

pokemon.name: Gallade
pokemon.pokedexX: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
pokemon.pokedexY: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

pokemon.name: Probopass
pokemon.pokedexX: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses
pokemon.pokedexY: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

pokemon.name: Dusknoir
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.
pokemon.pokedexY: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

pokemon.name: Froslass
pokemon.pokedexX: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.
pokemon.pokedexY: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

pokemon.name: Rotom
pokemon.pokedexX: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

pokemon.name: Uxie
pokemon.pokedexX: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

pokemon.name: Mesprit
pokemon.pokedexX: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
pokemon.pokedexY: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

pokemon.name: Azelf
pokemon.pokedexX: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit and Azelf all came from the same egg.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

pokemon.name: Dialga
pokemon.pokedexX: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

pokemon.name: Palkia
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

pokemon.name: Heatran
pokemon.pokedexX: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.
pokemon.pokedexY: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

pokemon.name: Regigigas
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.
pokemon.pokedexY: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.
pokemon.pokedexAS: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

pokemon.name: Giratina-Altered
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
pokemon.pokedexY: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

pokemon.name: Cresselia
pokemon.pokedexX: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
pokemon.pokedexY: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

pokemon.name: Phione
pokemon.pokedexX: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.
pokemon.pokedexY: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

pokemon.name: Manaphy
pokemon.pokedexX: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Darkrai
pokemon.pokedexX: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

pokemon.name: Shaymin-Land
pokemon.pokedexX: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
pokemon.pokedexY: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

pokemon.name: Arceus
pokemon.pokedexX: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.
pokemon.pokedexOR: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

pokemon.name: Victini
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

pokemon.name: Snivy
pokemon.pokedexX: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.
pokemon.pokedexY: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

pokemon.name: Servine
pokemon.pokedexX: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

pokemon.name: Serperior
pokemon.pokedexX: It only gives its all fighting against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can stop its opponents'movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

pokemon.name: Tepig
pokemon.pokedexX: It can deftly dodge its foe's attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.
pokemon.pokedexY: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can deftly dodge its foe's attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

pokemon.name: Pignite
pokemon.pokedexX: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.
pokemon.pokedexY: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

pokemon.name: Emboar
pokemon.pokedexX: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

pokemon.name: Oshawott
pokemon.pokedexX: The scalchop on its stomach isn't just used for battle--it can be used to break open hard berries as well.
pokemon.pokedexY: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The scalchop on its stomach isn't just used for battle-it can be used to break open hard berries as well.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

pokemon.name: Dewott
pokemon.pokedexX: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.
pokemon.pokedexY: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

pokemon.name: Samurott
pokemon.pokedexX: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.
pokemon.pokedexY: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.
