pokemon.pokedexAS: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

pokemon.name: Patrat
pokemon.pokedexX: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.
pokemon.pokedexY: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

pokemon.name: Watchog
pokemon.pokedexX: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.
pokemon.pokedexY: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

pokemon.name: Lillipup
pokemon.pokedexX: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.
pokemon.pokedexY: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.

pokemon.name: Herdier
pokemon.pokedexX: This very loyal Pokémon helps Trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This very loyal Pokémon helps Trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

pokemon.name: Stoutland
pokemon.pokedexX: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.
pokemon.pokedexY: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

pokemon.name: Purrloin
pokemon.pokedexX: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken, It attacks with sharp claws.
pokemon.pokedexY: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

pokemon.name: Liepard
pokemon.pokedexX: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
pokemon.pokedexY: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

pokemon.name: Pansage
pokemon.pokedexX: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.
pokemon.pokedexY: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

pokemon.name: Simisage
pokemon.pokedexX: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.
pokemon.pokedexY: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

pokemon.name: Pansear
pokemon.pokedexX: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.
pokemon.pokedexY: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Simisear
pokemon.pokedexX: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

pokemon.name: Panpour
pokemon.pokedexX: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

pokemon.name: Simipour
pokemon.pokedexX: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.
pokemon.pokedexY: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

pokemon.name: Munna
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.
pokemon.pokedexY: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

pokemon.name: Musharna
pokemon.pokedexX: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

pokemon.name: Pidove
pokemon.pokedexX: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.
pokemon.pokedexY: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.
pokemon.pokedexAS: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

pokemon.name: Tranquill
pokemon.pokedexX: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
pokemon.pokedexY: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets seperated from its Trainer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
pokemon.pokedexAS: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

pokemon.name: Unfezant
pokemon.pokedexX: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.
pokemon.pokedexY: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

pokemon.name: Blitzle
pokemon.pokedexX: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

pokemon.name: Zebstrika
pokemon.pokedexX: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.
pokemon.pokedexY: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

pokemon.name: Roggenrola
pokemon.pokedexX: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.
pokemon.pokedexY: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

pokemon.name: Boldore
pokemon.pokedexX: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked out and formed orange crystals.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.

pokemon.name: Gigalith
pokemon.pokedexX: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.
pokemon.pokedexY: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

pokemon.name: Woobat
pokemon.pokedexX: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits  ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.
pokemon.pokedexY: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

pokemon.name: Swoobat
pokemon.pokedexX: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
pokemon.pokedexY: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

pokemon.name: Drilbur
pokemon.pokedexX: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

pokemon.name: Excadrill
pokemon.pokedexX: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.
pokemon.pokedexY: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.
pokemon.pokedexAS: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

pokemon.name: Audino
pokemon.pokedexX: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
pokemon.pokedexY: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

pokemon.name: Timburr
pokemon.pokedexX: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.
pokemon.pokedexY: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.
pokemon.pokedexOR: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

pokemon.name: Gurdurr
pokemon.pokedexX: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.
pokemon.pokedexY: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.
pokemon.pokedexOR: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

pokemon.name: Conkeldurr
pokemon.pokedexX: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
pokemon.pokedexY: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

pokemon.name: Tympole
pokemon.pokedexX: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.
pokemon.pokedexY: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

pokemon.name: Palpitoad
pokemon.pokedexX: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

pokemon.name: Seismitoad
pokemon.pokedexX: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.
pokemon.pokedexY: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

pokemon.name: Throh
pokemon.pokedexX: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts
pokemon.pokedexY: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

pokemon.name: Sawk
pokemon.pokedexX: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.
pokemon.pokedexY: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

pokemon.name: Sewaddle
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexY: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

pokemon.name: Swadloon
pokemon.pokedexX: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
pokemon.pokedexY: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

pokemon.name: Leavanny
pokemon.pokedexX: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexY: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

pokemon.name: Venipede
pokemon.pokedexX: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

pokemon.name: Whirlipede
pokemon.pokedexX: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

pokemon.name: Scolipede
pokemon.pokedexX: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.
pokemon.pokedexY: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.
pokemon.pokedexAS: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

pokemon.name: Cottonee
pokemon.pokedexX: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.
pokemon.pokedexY: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

pokemon.name: Whimsicott
pokemon.pokedexX: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

pokemon.name: Petilil
pokemon.pokedexX: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.
pokemon.pokedexY: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

pokemon.name: Lilligant
pokemon.pokedexX: The fragrance if the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a trainer does not take good care of it.
pokemon.pokedexY: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

pokemon.name: Basculin-Red
pokemon.pokedexX: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.
pokemon.pokedexY: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.

pokemon.name: Sandile
pokemon.pokedexX: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.
pokemon.pokedexY: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

pokemon.name: Krokorok
pokemon.pokedexX: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.
pokemon.pokedexY: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.

pokemon.name: Krookodile
pokemon.pokedexX: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.
pokemon.pokedexY: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

pokemon.name: Darumaka
pokemon.pokedexX: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 F.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Darmanitan
pokemon.pokedexX: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

pokemon.name: Maractus
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds
pokemon.pokedexY: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

pokemon.name: Dwebble
pokemon.pokedexX: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

pokemon.name: Crustle
pokemon.pokedexX: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.
pokemon.pokedexY: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

pokemon.name: Scraggy
pokemon.pokedexX: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.
pokemon.pokedexY: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

pokemon.name: Scrafty
pokemon.pokedexX: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

pokemon.name: Sigilyph
pokemon.pokedexX: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.
pokemon.pokedexY: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

pokemon.name: Yamask
pokemon.pokedexX: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.
pokemon.pokedexY: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.
pokemon.pokedexOR: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

pokemon.name: Cofagrigus
pokemon.pokedexX: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.
pokemon.pokedexY: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

pokemon.name: Tirtouga
pokemon.pokedexX: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.
pokemon.pokedexOR: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

pokemon.name: Carracosta
pokemon.pokedexX: They can live in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.
pokemon.pokedexY: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

pokemon.name: Archen
pokemon.pokedexX: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

pokemon.name: Archeops
pokemon.pokedexX: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.
pokemon.pokedexY: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.

pokemon.name: Trubbish
pokemon.pokedexX: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

pokemon.name: Garbodor
pokemon.pokedexX: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexY: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

pokemon.name: Zorua
pokemon.pokedexX: It changes so it looks like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.
pokemon.pokedexY: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.
pokemon.pokedexAS: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Zoroark
pokemon.pokedexX: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
pokemon.pokedexY: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong.  It protects the safety of its pack by tricking  its opponents.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

pokemon.name: Minccino
pokemon.pokedexX: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails
pokemon.pokedexY: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.
pokemon.pokedexAS: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

pokemon.name: Cinccino
pokemon.pokedexX: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.
pokemon.pokedexY: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

pokemon.name: Gothita
pokemon.pokedexX: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.
pokemon.pokedexY: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

pokemon.name: Gothorita
pokemon.pokedexX: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.
pokemon.pokedexY: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.
pokemon.pokedexAS: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

pokemon.name: Gothitelle
pokemon.pokedexX: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.
pokemon.pokedexY: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

pokemon.name: Solosis
pokemon.pokedexX: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.
pokemon.pokedexY: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

pokemon.name: Duosion
pokemon.pokedexX: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.
pokemon.pokedexY: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

pokemon.name: Reuniclus
pokemon.pokedexX: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.
pokemon.pokedexY: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

pokemon.name: Ducklett
pokemon.pokedexX: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.
pokemon.pokedexY: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they  dive underwater.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

pokemon.name: Swanna
pokemon.pokedexX: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.
pokemon.pokedexY: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

pokemon.name: Vanillite
pokemon.pokedexX: The temperature of their breath is -58 degrees Fahrenheit. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the area around them.
pokemon.pokedexY: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The temperature of their breath is -58 degrees Fahrenheit. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

pokemon.name: Vanillish
pokemon.pokedexX: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

pokemon.name: Vanilluxe
pokemon.pokedexX: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.
pokemon.pokedexY: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

pokemon.name: Deerling
pokemon.pokedexX: Their coloring changes according to the season and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.
pokemon.pokedexY: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their coloring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

pokemon.name: Sawsbuck
pokemon.pokedexX: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck's horns
pokemon.pokedexY: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck's horns.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

pokemon.name: Emolga
pokemon.pokedexX: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.
pokemon.pokedexY: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

pokemon.name: Karrablast
pokemon.pokedexX: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.
pokemon.pokedexY: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.
pokemon.pokedexOR: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.
pokemon.pokedexAS: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

pokemon.name: Escavalier
pokemon.pokedexX: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.
pokemon.pokedexY: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.
pokemon.pokedexAS: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

pokemon.name: Foongus
pokemon.pokedexX: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

pokemon.name: Amoonguss
pokemon.pokedexX: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

pokemon.name: Frillish
pokemon.pokedexX: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.
pokemon.pokedexY: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

pokemon.name: Jellicent
pokemon.pokedexX: Its body is mostly seawater. It's said there's a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.
pokemon.pokedexY: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its body is mostly seawater. It's said there's a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

pokemon.name: Alomomola
pokemon.pokedexX: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.
pokemon.pokedexY: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

pokemon.name: Joltik
pokemon.pokedexX: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.
pokemon.pokedexY: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

pokemon.name: Galvantula
pokemon.pokedexX: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.
pokemon.pokedexY: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

pokemon.name: Ferroseed
pokemon.pokedexX: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.
pokemon.pokedexY: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

pokemon.name: Ferrothorn
pokemon.pokedexX: By swinging around its three spiky feelers and shooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.
pokemon.pokedexY: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By swinging around its three spiky feelers and shooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

pokemon.name: Klink
pokemon.pokedexX: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.
pokemon.pokedexY: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

pokemon.name: Klang
pokemon.pokedexX: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feeling to others. When angry, it rotates faster.
pokemon.pokedexY: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

pokemon.name: Klinklang
pokemon.pokedexX: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

pokemon.name: Tynamo
pokemon.pokedexX: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
pokemon.pokedexY: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.
pokemon.pokedexOR: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
pokemon.pokedexAS: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

pokemon.name: Eelektrik
pokemon.pokedexX: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.
pokemon.pokedexY: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.
pokemon.pokedexAS: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

pokemon.name: Eelektross
pokemon.pokedexX: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.
pokemon.pokedexY: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
pokemon.pokedexOR: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

pokemon.name: Elgyem
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent's brain, causing unendurable headaches.
pokemon.pokedexY: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent's brain, causing unendurable headaches.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

pokemon.name: Beheeyem
pokemon.pokedexX: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven't been decoded.
pokemon.pokedexY: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven't been decoded.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

pokemon.name: Litwick
pokemon.pokedexX: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.
pokemon.pokedexY: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

pokemon.name: Lampent
pokemon.pokedexX: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.
pokemon.pokedexY: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

pokemon.name: Chandelure
pokemon.pokedexX: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.
pokemon.pokedexY: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

pokemon.name: Axew
pokemon.pokedexX: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
pokemon.pokedexY: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

pokemon.name: Fraxure
pokemon.pokedexX: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.
pokemon.pokedexY: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

pokemon.name: Haxorus
pokemon.pokedexX: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
pokemon.pokedexY: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

pokemon.name: Cubchoo
pokemon.pokedexX: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.
pokemon.pokedexY: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthly, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

pokemon.name: Beartic
pokemon.pokedexX: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways across the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.
pokemon.pokedexY: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways across the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

pokemon.name: Cryogonal
pokemon.pokedexX: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
pokemon.pokedexY: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Shelmet
pokemon.pokedexX: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.
pokemon.pokedexY: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

pokemon.name: Accelgor
pokemon.pokedexX: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.
pokemon.pokedexY: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

pokemon.name: Stunfisk
pokemon.pokedexX: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
pokemon.pokedexY: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

pokemon.name: Mienfoo
pokemon.pokedexX: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.
pokemon.pokedexY: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

pokemon.name: Mienshao
pokemon.pokedexX: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot ever be seen.
pokemon.pokedexY: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

pokemon.name: Druddigon
pokemon.pokedexX: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
pokemon.pokedexY: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

pokemon.name: Golett
pokemon.pokedexX: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.
pokemon.pokedexY: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

pokemon.name: Golurk
pokemon.pokedexX: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

pokemon.name: Pawniard
pokemon.pokedexX: Blades comprise this Pokémon's entire body.  If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.
pokemon.pokedexY: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Blades comprise this Pokémon's entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

pokemon.name: Bisharp
pokemon.pokedexX: The pitiless Pokémon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.
pokemon.pokedexY: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

pokemon.name: Bouffalant
pokemon.pokedexX: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.
pokemon.pokedexY: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

pokemon.name: Rufflet
pokemon.pokedexX: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.
pokemon.pokedexY: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

pokemon.name: Braviary
pokemon.pokedexX: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
pokemon.pokedexY: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.
pokemon.pokedexOR: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

pokemon.name: Vullaby
pokemon.pokedexX: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.
pokemon.pokedexY: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

pokemon.name: Mandibuzz
pokemon.pokedexX: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.
pokemon.pokedexY: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

pokemon.name: Heatmor
pokemon.pokedexX: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.
pokemon.pokedexY: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

pokemon.name: Durant
pokemon.pokedexX: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.
pokemon.pokedexY: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

pokemon.name: Deino
pokemon.pokedexX: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds
pokemon.pokedexY: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

pokemon.name: Zweilous
pokemon.pokedexX: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.
pokemon.pokedexY: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.
pokemon.pokedexAS: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

pokemon.name: Hydreigon
pokemon.pokedexX: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.
pokemon.pokedexY: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!
pokemon.pokedexOR: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

pokemon.name: Larvesta
pokemon.pokedexX: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.
pokemon.pokedexY: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

pokemon.name: Volcarona
pokemon.pokedexX: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.
pokemon.pokedexY: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.

pokemon.name: Cobalion
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Terrakion
pokemon.pokedexX: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.
pokemon.pokedexY: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Virizion
pokemon.pokedexX: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
pokemon.pokedexY: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

pokemon.name: Tornadus-Incarnate
pokemon.pokedexX: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
pokemon.pokedexY: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

pokemon.name: Thundurus-Incarnate
pokemon.pokedexX: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexY: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

pokemon.name: Reshiram
pokemon.pokedexX: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.
pokemon.pokedexY: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

pokemon.name: Zekrom
pokemon.pokedexX: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.
pokemon.pokedexY: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

pokemon.name: Landorus-Incarnate
pokemon.pokedexX: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."
pokemon.pokedexY: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."
pokemon.pokedexAS: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

pokemon.name: Kyurem
pokemon.pokedexX: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.
pokemon.pokedexY: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

pokemon.name: Keldeo
pokemon.pokedexX: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

pokemon.name: Meloetta-Aria
pokemon.pokedexX: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

pokemon.name: Genesect
pokemon.pokedexX: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
pokemon.pokedexY: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

pokemon.name: Chespin
pokemon.pokedexX: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.
pokemon.pokedexY: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.
