pokemon.name: Quilladin
pokemon.pokedexX: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators' attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.
pokemon.pokedexY: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators' attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

pokemon.name: Chesnaught
pokemon.pokedexX: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

pokemon.name: Fennekin
pokemon.pokedexX: Eating a twig fills it with energy,  and its roomy ears give vent to air  hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexY: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

pokemon.name: Braixen
pokemon.pokedexX: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With  friction from its tail fur, it sets the  twig on fire and launches into battle.
pokemon.pokedexY: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

pokemon.name: Delphox
pokemon.pokedexX: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.
pokemon.pokedexY: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

pokemon.name: Froakie
pokemon.pokedexX: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.
pokemon.pokedexY: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Frogadier
pokemon.pokedexX: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

pokemon.name: Greninja
pokemon.pokedexX: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.
pokemon.pokedexY: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

pokemon.name: Bunnelby
pokemon.pokedexX: They use their large ears to dig burrows.  They will dig the whole night through.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

pokemon.name: Diggersby
pokemon.pokedexX: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.
pokemon.pokedexY: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.
pokemon.pokedexOR: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.
pokemon.pokedexAS: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

pokemon.name: Fletchling
pokemon.pokedexX: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.
pokemon.pokedexY: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.
pokemon.pokedexOR: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.

pokemon.name: Fletchinder
pokemon.pokedexX: From its beak, it expels embers that set  the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on  the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.
pokemon.pokedexY: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.
pokemon.pokedexOR: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

pokemon.name: Talonflame
pokemon.pokedexX: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.
pokemon.pokedexY: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.

pokemon.name: Scatterbug
pokemon.pokedexX: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.
pokemon.pokedexY: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

pokemon.name: Spewpa
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur  covering its body in an effort to threaten them.
pokemon.pokedexY: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

pokemon.name: Vivillon
pokemon.pokedexX: Vivillon with many different patterns are  found all over the world. These patterns  are affected by the climate of their habitat.
pokemon.pokedexY: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

pokemon.name: Litleo
pokemon.pokedexX: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.
pokemon.pokedexY: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

pokemon.name: Pyroar
pokemon.pokedexX: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.
pokemon.pokedexY: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.
pokemon.pokedexAS: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.

pokemon.name: Flabébé
pokemon.pokedexX: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.
pokemon.pokedexY: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.

pokemon.name: Floette
pokemon.pokedexX: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the power of flowers to battle.
pokemon.pokedexY: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the power of flowers to battle.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

pokemon.name: Florges
pokemon.pokedexX: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.
pokemon.pokedexY: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.

pokemon.name: Skiddo
pokemon.pokedexX: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it has sunshine and water, it doesnt need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

pokemon.name: Gogoat
pokemon.pokedexX: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.
pokemon.pokedexY: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

pokemon.name: Pancham
pokemon.pokedexX: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.
pokemon.pokedexY: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.

pokemon.name: Pangoro
pokemon.pokedexX: Although it posses a violent temperament, it won't put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.
pokemon.pokedexY: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won't put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

pokemon.name: Furfrou
pokemon.pokedexX: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes  it more elegant but also increases the  swiftness of its movements.
pokemon.pokedexY: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

pokemon.name: Espurr
pokemon.pokedexX: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

pokemon.name: Meowstic-M
pokemon.pokedexX: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.
pokemon.pokedexY: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

pokemon.name: Honedge
pokemon.pokedexX: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.
pokemon.pokedexY: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

pokemon.name: Doublade
pokemon.pokedexX: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.
pokemon.pokedexY: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

pokemon.name: Aegislash-Shield
pokemon.pokedexX: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexY: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

pokemon.name: Spritzee
pokemon.pokedexX: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragance changes depending on what it has eaten.
pokemon.pokedexY: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

pokemon.name: Aromatisse
pokemon.pokedexX: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

pokemon.name: Swirlix
pokemon.pokedexX: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes  white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.
pokemon.pokedexY: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.
pokemon.pokedexOR: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

pokemon.name: Slurpuff
pokemon.pokedexX: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

pokemon.name: Inkay
pokemon.pokedexX: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the  light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.

pokemon.name: Malamar
pokemon.pokedexX: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.
pokemon.pokedexY: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

pokemon.name: Binacle
pokemon.pokedexX: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.
pokemon.pokedexY: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat  seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.
pokemon.pokedexAS: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

pokemon.name: Barbaracle
pokemon.pokedexX: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.
pokemon.pokedexY: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

pokemon.name: Skrelp
pokemon.pokedexX: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.
pokemon.pokedexY: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

pokemon.name: Dragalge
pokemon.pokedexX: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.
pokemon.pokedexY: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.

pokemon.name: Clauncher
pokemon.pokedexX: They knock down flying prey by firing  compressed water from their massive  claws like shooting a pistol.
pokemon.pokedexY: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

pokemon.name: Clawitzer
pokemon.pokedexX: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.
pokemon.pokedexY: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

pokemon.name: Helioptile
pokemon.pokedexX: They make their home in deserts. They can  generate their energy from basking in the sun,  so eating food is not a requirement.
pokemon.pokedexY: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

pokemon.name: Heliolisk
pokemon.pokedexX: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.
pokemon.pokedexY: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

pokemon.name: Tyrunt
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn't like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn't like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.

pokemon.name: Tyrantrum
pokemon.pokedexX: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.
pokemon.pokedexY: Nothing could stop this Pokémon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Nothing could stop this Pokémon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.

pokemon.name: Amaura
pokemon.pokedexX: This ancient Pokémon was restored  from part of its body that had been  frozen in ice for over 100 million years.
pokemon.pokedexY: This calm Pokémon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This calm Pokémon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.

pokemon.name: Aurorus
pokemon.pokedexX: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.
pokemon.pokedexY: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.

pokemon.name: Sylveon
pokemon.pokedexX: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.
pokemon.pokedexY: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.

pokemon.name: Hawlucha
pokemon.pokedexX: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.
pokemon.pokedexY: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.
pokemon.pokedexAS: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

pokemon.name: Dedenne
pokemon.pokedexX: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and  receiving electrical waves, it can communicate  with others over vast distances.
pokemon.pokedexY: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

pokemon.name: Carbink
pokemon.pokedexX: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

pokemon.name: Goomy
pokemon.pokedexX: The weakest Dragon-Type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn't dry out.
pokemon.pokedexY: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn't dry out.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.

pokemon.name: Sliggoo
pokemon.pokedexX: It drives away opponents by excreting a  sticky liquid that can dissolve anything.  Its eyes devolved, so it can't see anything.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can't see anything.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.

pokemon.name: Goodra
pokemon.pokedexX: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.
pokemon.pokedexY: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.

pokemon.name: Klefki
pokemon.pokedexX: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.
pokemon.pokedexY: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.
pokemon.pokedexOR: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

pokemon.name: Phantump
pokemon.pokedexX: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.
pokemon.pokedexY: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.
pokemon.pokedexOR: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.
pokemon.pokedexAS: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

pokemon.name: Trevenant
pokemon.pokedexX: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.
pokemon.pokedexY: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

pokemon.name: Pumpkaboo-Average
pokemon.pokedexX: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.

pokemon.name: Gourgeist-Average
pokemon.pokedexX: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.
pokemon.pokedexY: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

pokemon.name: Bergmite
pokemon.pokedexX: It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.
pokemon.pokedexY: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

pokemon.name: Avalugg
pokemon.pokedexX: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.
pokemon.pokedexY: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.

pokemon.name: Noibat
pokemon.pokedexX: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.
pokemon.pokedexY: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

pokemon.name: Noivern
pokemon.pokedexX: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.
pokemon.pokedexY: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.
pokemon.pokedexOR: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

pokemon.name: Xerneas
pokemon.pokedexX: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.
pokemon.pokedexY: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.
pokemon.pokedexAS: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

pokemon.name: Yveltal
pokemon.pokedexX: When this legendary Pokémon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.
pokemon.pokedexY: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

pokemon.name: Volcanion

pokemon.pokedexOR: Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Castform borrows the power of nature to transform itself into the guises of the sun, rain, and snow-clouds. This Pokémon's feelings change with the weather.

pokemon.pokedexAS: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

pokemon.pokedexOR: There is a large flower on Venusaur's back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.

pokemon.name: Charizard-Mega-X
pokemon.pokedexX: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.

pokemon.name: Blastoise-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
pokemon.pokedexY: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokémon's shell are used for high-speed tackles.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

pokemon.name: Alakazam-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Its brain cells multiply continually until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Alakazam's brain continually grows, infinitely multiplying brain cells. This amazing brain gives this Pokémon an astoundingly high IQ of 5,000. It has a thorough memory of everything that has occurred in the world.

pokemon.name: Gengar-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It hides in shadows. It is said that if Gengar is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemon.pokedexY: Hiding in people's shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.

pokemon.name: Kangaskhan-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.
pokemon.pokedexOR: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.
pokemon.pokedexAS: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.

pokemon.name: Pinsir-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.
pokemon.pokedexY: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack.  During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokémon's movements turn sluggish in cold places.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Pinsir has a pair of massive horns. Protruding from the surface of these horns are thorns. These thorns are driven deeply into the foe's body when the pincer closes, making it tough for the foe to escape.

pokemon.name: Gyarados-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: In ancient literature, there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared.
pokemon.pokedexY: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Once Gyarados goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn't calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this Pokémon's rampages lasting a whole month.

pokemon.name: Aerodactyl-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It was regenerated from a dinosaur's genetic matter that was found in amber. It flies with high-pitched cries.
pokemon.pokedexY: This vicious Pokémon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.

pokemon.name: Mewtwo-Mega-X

pokemon.pokedexY: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

pokemon.pokedexOR: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon's body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

pokemon.name: Ampharos-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
pokemon.pokedexY: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from  far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

pokemon.name: Scizor-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: This Pokémon's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets ahold of into bits.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

pokemon.name: Heracross-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies, then lifts and throws them.
pokemon.pokedexY: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe's grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Heracross has sharp claws on its feet. These are planted firmly into the ground or the bark of a tree, giving the Pokémon a secure and solid footing to forcefully fling away foes with its proud horn.

pokemon.name: Houndoom-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.
pokemon.pokedexY: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins.  If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.
pokemon.pokedexAS: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

pokemon.name: Tyranitar-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.
pokemon.pokedexY: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries  rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

pokemon.name: Blaziken-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs it jump clear over buildings.
pokemon.pokedexOR: In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon's wrists burn.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs-it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon's blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

pokemon.name: Gardevoir-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
pokemon.pokedexY: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Gardevoir has the psychokinetic power to distort the dimensions and create a small black hole. This Pokémon will try to protect its Trainer even at the risk of its own life.

pokemon.name: Mawile-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.
pokemon.pokedexY: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Don't be taken in by this Pokémon's cute face-it's very dangerous. Mawile fools the foe into letting down its guard, then chomps down with its massive jaws. The steel jaws are really horns that have been transformed.

pokemon.name: Aggron-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don't take it lightly.
pokemon.pokedexY: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by  breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Aggron claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This Pokémon vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Aggron is protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this Pokémon will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

pokemon.name: Medicham-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the  same motion.
pokemon.pokedexY: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Through the power of meditation, Medicham developed its sixth sense. It gained the ability to use psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon is known to meditate for a whole month without eating.

pokemon.name: Manectric-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.
pokemon.pokedexY: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Manectric discharges strong electricity from its mane. The mane is used for collecting electricity in the atmosphere. This Pokémon creates thunderclouds above its head.

pokemon.name: Banette-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.
pokemon.pokedexY: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokémon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A cursed energy permeated the stuffing of a discarded and forgotten plush doll, giving it new life as Banette. The Pokémon's energy would escape if it were to ever open its mouth.

pokemon.name: Absol-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.
pokemon.pokedexY: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Absol has the ability to foretell the coming of natural disasters. It lives in a harsh, rugged mountain environment. This Pokémon very rarely ventures down from the mountains.

pokemon.name: Garchomp-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flies at speeds equals to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.
pokemon.pokedexOR: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

pokemon.name: Lucario-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.
pokemon.pokedexY: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.
pokemon.pokedexOR: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

pokemon.name: Abomasnow-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."
pokemon.pokedexY: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.
pokemon.pokedexOR: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."
pokemon.pokedexAS: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

pokemon.name: Beedrill-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
pokemon.pokedexY: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest-this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest-this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.
pokemon.pokedexY: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.
pokemon.pokedexOR: This Pokémon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: This Pokémon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Slowbro-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: An attached Shellder won't let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.
pokemon.pokedexY: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.

pokemon.name: Steelix-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.
pokemon.pokedexY: It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

pokemon.name: Sceptile-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: The leaves on its forelegs are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike.
pokemon.pokedexY: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.
pokemon.pokedexOR: The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile-it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sceptile has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This Pokémon raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

pokemon.name: Swampert-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Its arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down its foe. It makes its nest on beautiful beaches.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Swampert predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

pokemon.name: Sableye-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.
pokemon.pokedexY: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Sableye lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these Pokémon are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sableye digs the ground with sharpened claws to find rocks that it eats. Substances in the eaten rocks crystallize and rise up to the Pokémon's body surface.

pokemon.name: Sharpedo-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."
pokemon.pokedexY: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Nicknamed "the bully of the sea," Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This Pokémon's drawback is its inability to swim long distances.

pokemon.name: Camerupt-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.
pokemon.pokedexY: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The humps on Camerupt's back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokémon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

pokemon.name: Altaria-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you're in a dream.
pokemon.pokedexY: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and  blends into the clouds. It sings in a  beautiful soprano.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this Pokémon makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokémon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

pokemon.name: Glalie-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: To protect itself, it clad its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Glalie has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its prey solid. After immobilizing its prey in ice, this Pokémon enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.

pokemon.name: Salamence-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.
pokemon.pokedexY: It's uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Salamence came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this Pokémon's cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.
pokemon.pokedexAS: By evolving into Salamence, this Pokémon finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Metagross-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: With four linked brains, it's more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.
pokemon.pokedexY: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokémon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Metagross is the result of two Metang achieving fusion. When hunting, this Pokémon pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large mouth on its stomach.

pokemon.name: Latias-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.
pokemon.pokedexY: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

pokemon.name: Latios-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
pokemon.pokedexY: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

pokemon.name: Kyogre-Primal
pokemon.pokedexX: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon
pokemon.pokedexY: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

pokemon.name: Groudon-Primal
pokemon.pokedexX: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre
pokemon.pokedexY: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
pokemon.pokedexAS: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

pokemon.name: Rayquaza-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
pokemon.pokedexY: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

pokemon.name: Lopunny-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
pokemon.pokedexY: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
pokemon.pokedexAS: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

pokemon.name: Gallade
pokemon.pokedexX: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
pokemon.pokedexY: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

pokemon.name: Gallade-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
pokemon.pokedexY: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
pokemon.pokedexAS: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

pokemon.name: Audino-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
pokemon.pokedexY: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
pokemon.pokedexOR: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

pokemon.name: Diancie-Mega
pokemon.pokedexX: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.
pokemon.pokedexY: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
pokemon.pokedexOR: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.
pokemon.pokedexAS: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
